rly_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1452340800.0} {"text": "Good", "appid": "457140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032589475", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "hot dog this game is funny as ♥♥♥♥ love it!!!!", "appid": "402330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198112200276", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1463054400.0} {"text": "10/10 Epilepsy simulator", "appid": "296070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198036445124", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1423310400.0} {"text": "All I can say is its more Bloon popping fun and very addictive and its FREE to play, now were did all those hours go :O Just want to also add Its NOT a pay to win game, you DONT need to spend any money in this game although I did buy 1 farmer which is all you need and some dlcs when they where 80% off in the 2020 June sale. You DONT need to buy anything to enjoy this game, unless your happy to help support these developers. There is contested land you can try win and hold for set amount of times, before the balloons take the land back, if you get to certain rounds you win gold bloongems and knowledge chests etc. You never need to spend any real money even though you can if you choose to. I also very much enjoy playing this game, seems more enjoyable than Bloons TD 6 guess I lost interest in Bloons TD 6 for now :) Also if you buy any dlcs from the store, the game should be locked to your account, only buy when 80% off or more as they dont offer much in content which I found, they are only decorations for your city.", "appid": "1252780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079335824", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596628800.0} {"text": "What is there to say... Best sport game of the decade, mixing with amazing racing engine, that is elevated with amazing mechanics! Which makes it also, the best E-sport around! Let just hope Epic won't screw things up! Highly recommended", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996737690", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0} {"text": "so good", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198318518857", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1478520000.0} {"text": "It's censored YES! but it still is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ hot. Just being honest. 7/10 amazing fap material!", "appid": "626330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198106498416", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514203200.0} {"text": "10/10", "appid": "107410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198125805212", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "19", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "此游戏的key自 获得，感谢开发者与相关社区工作人员的努力。 + 以物流为核心的玩法框架 + 细节到位的low poly画风 - 缺乏激励的生涯模式 - 数值方面欠缺打磨 - 微妙的寻路AI 总评：6.5/10，在激励机制方面存在巨大缺陷的生产链经营模拟游戏，初见很有趣，越玩越无聊。 常驻我电脑之中的《Simcity》、《Factorio》、《Rimworld》，有一种魔性，无论是清晨还是傍晚，只要你打开这些游戏，就会像被蒙住眼睛、闻着胡萝卜味道的驴子一样，围着游戏小小平衡打着转，等你建立了新的循环，看一眼时间，才会发觉已经一天过去了... 我称呼这种游戏为Loop Game，或者叫流水线/生产链/生态圈模拟游戏，它们往往有复杂的数值系统，要玩家从无到有，建议一个自给自足的循环体系，并不断添加新的元素，让玩家打破旧有的循环，扩展原来的链条...如此循环。从游戏类型与宣传上来看，《Rise of Industry》也应该是这样一个充满魔性的loop game？我准备好了一天的空闲、怀着这样的期待打开游戏。 但我的期待落空了。 在《Rise of Industry》中，玩家要以公路、铁路、水运等物流渠道为核心，一步步解锁新的工业建筑，建立一个从农矿原材料到电子工业产品产品的庞大工业体系。low poly风格、每种建筑均有独立动画、广阔的沙盘、极简的UI，虽然在数值和寻路AI方面有一些小小的问题，但整体看起来很不错，是吧？是一块消磨时间的好“磨盘”。 那驴子为什么站在原地，一动不动？ 因为没有美味的胡萝卜呀。 在loop类游戏中，“胡萝卜”是必不可少的。它可能是竞争对手、宇宙海盗、季节变化、巨额订单，催促着玩家补全循环中的一个个小链条，可以说，这根“胡萝卜”才是loop game的核心魅力所在。《Rise of Industry》的开发者自然是明白这个道理的，他们在生涯模式中加入了解锁建筑的科技树、多种多样的运输方式以及变化不定的市场价格，希望借此吸引玩家。 悲伤的是，我这头驴子被蒙着眼睛，只能闻到发臭的萝卜干味：看似自由的科技树实际上非常死板，而且都是构建工业体系的必须链条，并非可选内容；波动的市场价格受玩家的影响并不明显，经常出现大批出货反而促使产品涨价，囤积居奇价格反而大降到底的状况，玩家也无法直观地了解到竞争对手——如果那些默默生产的工厂算的话——的变化，像是一个人在过家家；多元化的运输方式差距并不明显，感觉就是换个模型调整一下数值...这样的“萝卜干”，怎么能吸引贪食的我，啊不，驴子？ 好了，吐槽完毕，整体而言，该游戏是一部合格，但有重大缺陷的物流生产链建设模拟游戏。若你对构建循环的模拟游戏感兴趣，那么《Rise of Industry》大概能给你带来3-10个小时的良好游戏体验，但如果想沉浸其中...萝卜干的臭味会让你止步的。", "appid": "671440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198169299825", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1520856000.0} {"text": "Bom jogo.", "appid": "227300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198319647030", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556280000.0} {"text": "Шедевр!!!! в начале конечно диалогов овер много которые рекомендую просто скипать) А так игра очень интересная к управлению привыкаешь спустя 1 час", "appid": "626690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198191523877", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1519387200.0} {"text": "Battle Royal richtig richtig geil für das das das Spiel in der Alpha is Daumen hoch!", "appid": "295110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198156976923", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1436616000.0} {"text": "amaazing", "appid": "386940", "steamid": "profiles/76561197973210732", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576843200.0} {"text": "GOOOD,....just GOOOD", "appid": "4000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198093191960", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1427716800.0} {"text": "Efsane ol bir sarıyo misss", "appid": "1259970", "steamid": "profiles/76561199057948053", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602590400.0} {"text": "good ♥♥♥♥ with friends", "appid": "1250", "steamid": "profiles/76561198109756202", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1522411200.0} {"text": "Los efectos de sonido son maravillosos.", "appid": "435400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198201132203", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545998400.0} {"text": "its aight", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060615179", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577620800.0} {"text": "Написать отзыв только через шесть лет - без[c]ценно. Особенно вспомнить про это в пятницу 13-е) И опубликовать в 13:13. Касаемо сабжа - вечная классика шутеров. Всем хороших каток и добра по жизни))", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198013522288", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1568376000.0} {"text": "Muy buen juego", "appid": "78000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198242025590", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1457006400.0} {"text": "Игра просто пуше4ка", "appid": "1046930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198985483317", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586433600.0} {"text": "Жил до конца,умер как герой!", "appid": "583950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198050501995", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575028800.0} {"text": "its so confusing but i learnt how to play it later on", "appid": "682290", "steamid": "profiles/76561197969496762", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1538913600.0} {"text": "Eski Sitemimde Çok düşük Fps lerde bitirmiştim yeni sistem topladım tekrar bitireceğim", "appid": "220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198368703955", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "MARCIN TO HIPSER.", "appid": "105600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198251631810", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528632000.0} {"text": "great war tps game (y)", "appid": "50300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198145917965", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1480334400.0} {"text": "Infuriating in the most delightful way Life Is Strange​ is possibly one of the greatest games I have ever played. Never before have I found the decisions you make in a game have such massive consequences (not like the end of Mass Effect...) There is usually no obvious option which is a real skill for a game to pull off. I find myself getting very emotionally invested in the story and the characters which for me is a such sign of a good game! The graphics are not mind-blowing but the graphic style really suits the concept of the game. The game balances the moments of real hard decision making with the beautiful moments of serenity and introspective thought. The soundtrack is simply divine and truly captures the potency of the important moments as well as providing the most natural of backdrops for the game in general. The dialogue does sometimes feel just a little unnatural but certain not so as to ruin the game. When I first saw the game on Steam back in February I was instantly intrigued. It took me until May to play it as I had a feeling I would be drawn in to the game too much for my own good. I was right.", "appid": "319630", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985926603", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1433160000.0} {"text": "This game got everything you need or want: Bloody butcher, nice weapons, fast and intense rounds and it takes a good teamplay. I'm just saying thumbs up and stay alive!!!", "appid": "232090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004793035", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511697600.0} {"text": "Игра хз какая,я не играл xD", "appid": "1089710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198314771590", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "В РБ остался один против бобра, увидел точку, и начал за ней лететь, летал 10 минут, 20 минут, 30 минут, а потом оказалось это пятно на экране", "appid": "236390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198247533806", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1483444800.0} {"text": "I like it. And I approve it. (type R18 to make it uncensored)", "appid": "927890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138049619", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544875200.0} {"text": "UBERMOSH:OMEGA is already the eigth game in the series, where you take control of a character, with their specificities, and try to ascend to the OMEGA rank. It's a fast-paced retro arcade game, where you must survive the longer you can so that you can score enough KO (killing enemies) to reach that rank, in a limited arena full of enemies. The six characters introduced in the previous game are back but now, you don't need to level them up for more strength and powers. They retain nearly all their characteristics from Vol 7: * Aya is the polyvalent one, with all the powers (melter, shredder, manastrike, brainclap). She's the core of UBERMOSH series. She is one of the three characters that can use a blade. * Wook can now use brainclap and is still using Onslaught as special power. The Autogun feature (flying gun) is still present and he's quick to upgrade the single flying gun to four of them. * T7 is still the reminder of the former GUNNER mode: only keeping your finger on the left-click to fire without difficulty. He has the Double Strike feature (two weapons) and still has tentacles as special attack. He's still brainclapping. * Q is the only one that can't grab a gun, a reminder to the former KENSAI mode. However, her long blade (or a double blade) is useful to cut bullets more efficiently. She's still brainclapping and using the double/triple melter * Kore is autofiring his gun, uses the Triple Strike and spawns directly with the four flying guns and he's still brainclapping. * Reez is spawning with a gun and a double-edge blade and she's still brainclapping and equipped with manastrike. However, you can choose to customize them with two extra gameplays. All of them have different customizations, however, here are the possibilities: * Up to two extra respawns (as you spawn with four by default) - all * Celerity to move faster - all * Warmup shield for the first ten seconds of a round - Aya, Wook, Kore * Late shield for the last ten seconds of a round - Wook, T7, Q, Kore, Reez * Buckler, a shield deflecting bullets - All except Reez * Shredder - All except Aya who has it naturally * Boneblade, a long-range blade - Aya, Reez * Autogun, the flying gun - All except Wook and Kore who spawn with them - Q is the only one that can choose twice the feature * Warlock, where the character spawns with a Warlock rifle - All except Q who can't grab gun Also, there is a new enemy: a shielded warrior, with the Warlock rifle, able to send multiple shredders and appearing at the same time as the shielder warrior with the same gun. There are no new weapons if you except the Boneblade. Walter Machado, the developer, comes back to what we loved also from UBERMOSH: the possibility to customize the gameplay as we wish to reach the OMEGA Rank, which was kinda missing in Vol 7. The whole way to progress has also turned back to the root of the series, instead of how Vol 7 was working: unlocking feature or improving skills by reaching a specific number of KO. I'm still trying to reach 100% with Wook in the previous game, which is the character I had the harder time to play. The graphics are still the same, even if the characters changed a little from the previous game. It's still that retrogaming feels, with pixels. The soundtrack is still the same. I love UBERMOSH and the whole series, even if I can agree that some of the titles could have been DLC instead of games. Here, the difference between Vol 7 and OMEGA are enough to justify a new game. However, I'm quite curious to see if we're going to have a new game or not. Because OMEGA is the best UBERMOSH game that Walter provided and I feel that everything after could suffer from that excellency (for me anyway). True, I would consider UBERMOSH:OMEGA like the UBERMOSH game you must play. But playing the first title of the series would also give you a real glance at the evolution of the games. Fans of the series will be satisfied, newcomers will enjoy the game as there are enough options to try. Really, a giant applause for Walter, who really outdid themselves this time.", "appid": "1181000", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971532357", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581854400.0} {"text": "OK", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198250440730", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1471435200.0} {"text": "Really nice game<3", "appid": "211050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198971459140", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574942400.0} {"text": "9/10 gra zajebista grafika mega zdecydowanie nie jest latwa. grac mozna multi jak i single player. swiat wielki a budowanie bardzo rozwiniete. wada jest umieranie na multi bo resetuje ci inventory :( ale ogolnie zajefajna", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198233631436", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1467028800.0} {"text": "You may write me down in history With your bitter, twisted lies, You may tread me in the very dirt But still, like dust, I'll rise. Does my sassiness upset you? Why are you beset with gloom? 'Cause I walk like I've got oil wells Pumping in my living room. Just like moons and like suns, With the certainty of tides, Just like hopes springing high, Still I'll rise. Did you want to see me broken? Bowed head and lowered eyes? Shoulders falling down like teardrops. Weakened by my soulful cries. Does my haughtiness offend you? Don't you take it awful hard 'Cause I laugh like I've got gold mines Diggin' in my own back yard. You may shoot me with your words, You may cut me with your eyes, You may kill me with your hatefulness, But still, like air, I'll rise. Does my sexiness upset you? Does it come as a surprise That I dance like I've got diamonds At the meeting of my thighs? Out of the huts of history's shame I rise Up from a past that's rooted in pain I rise I'm a black ocean, leaping and wide, Welling and swelling I bear in the tide. Leaving behind nights of terror and fear I rise Into a daybreak that's wondrously clear I rise Bringing the gifts that my ancestors gave, I am the dream and the hope of the slave. I rise I rise I rise.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198136268981", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543406400.0} {"text": "They don't let you pick up Nisha's hat to gift it to Fiona. And she is dreaming about the cool new hat all the time. What a shame. 2/10 but maah haaat", "appid": "330830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077970129", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1443182400.0} {"text": "10/10", "appid": "584400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198313086237", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1504094400.0} {"text": "Its a great and fun game with friends but you guys should realy update the launcher,it looks very outdated", "appid": "321400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198111837646", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554897600.0} {"text": "carzy but u need to watch it", "appid": "374570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124448247", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1433160000.0} {"text": "Mirror's Edge - игра, которая в определённой мере была в далёком 2009-м если и не переворотом, то как минимум глотком свежего воздуха в геймдеве. У неё довольно слабый сюжет с блеклыми персонажами, которые вообще никак не прописаны, посему сопереживать никому из них не хочется, но фишка игра была вовсе не в истории, она здесь для галочки. Главная прелесть игры - это геймплей. Mirror's Edge - ураганный экшен от первого лица, в котором ловко сплетаются акробатические задачи и динамичные бои. В то время подобное было в новинку, хотя игра и сейчас может порадовать новых игроков. Все эти пробежки, прыжки с крыши на крышу, драки с полицейскими настолько динамичны, что дух захватывают! Теперь к ложке дёгтя: игра и на лёгкой сложности порой кажется довольно трудной. Лично у меня были редкие моменты, которые приходилось переигрывать чуть ли не по десять раз: то врагов слишком много, то не сообразишь сразу, как/куда бежать, то упомянутые выше акробатические задачи оказываются довольно хитрыми, то натыкаешься на откровенные просчёты геймдизайна, то, казалось бы, прыгаешь в нужном направлении, но Фейт пролетает мимо и превращается в лепёшку. Ещё хотелось бы отметить, что у игры довольно приятная и по сей день картинка, но иной раз слишком вырвиглазно яркая (особенность освещения и геймдизайна). И напоследок - игра прямо-таки очень короткая, состоит из девяти эпизодов, которые пробегаются в зависимости от ваших навыков за 2-4 часа. Не успеет надоесть, конечно, но... Тем не менее Mirror's Edge - неплохая игра для своего времени, которая всё ещё приятно смотрится и играется. В составе подписки EA Play очень даже стоит внимания даже в 2020 году, но покупать отдельно с таким-то ценником весьма короткую игру 2009 года я категорически не советую. 6/10", "appid": "17410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043728491", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605441600.0} {"text": "взлом квадратной жопы", "appid": "706990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198826307225", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "кака", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198986821407", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1578657600.0} {"text": "this game is sick", "appid": "346110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198283911071", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572696000.0} {"text": "Best fps", "appid": "400790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198275244713", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500724800.0} {"text": "great", "appid": "48700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198831029564", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577534400.0} {"text": "Una cosa te digo... Dos escopetas tengo.", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198264066828", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562155200.0} {"text": "Одна из игр всех времен) p.s. играл еще в Titan Quest Gold и очень приятно видеть переиздание)", "appid": "475150", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961392478", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1483272000.0} {"text": "Empezaré por lo obvio, al menos por lo que me parece obvio a criterio personal. Dear Esther, no es un juego, si buscas jugar algo o al menos interactuar de alguna forma, pues de eso se trata o debería tratarse un videojuego, pues pasa de esta obra de The Chinese Room, puesto que acá lo único que encontrarás es una historia corta en formato audiovisual. Como producto artístico diré que Dear Esther hace méritos, una narrativa de carácter casi poético, un arte gráfico sobrecogedor que en lo personal me ha parecido notable, podrías sacarte unos cuantos excelentes wallpapers para tu PC de acá, pero lastimosamente toda la \"jugabilidad\", si se le podría llamar de esa forma, consiste en ir de un punto inicial a un punto final, en un sendero lineal, donde de cuando en cuando te narran la historia motivo de esta obra digital. No podría decir que la experiencia me disgustó, es más me encantaría una versión VR de Dear Esther, pues disfrutaría a lo grande paseándome por esta isla en un modo con el grado de inmersión que proporciona la realidad virtual, pues la ambientación no tiene desperdicio, esa sensación de horror cósmico que caldea alrededor es fabulosa y es una lástima que no se haya aprovechado todo esto para hacer algo mucho más memorable en el sentido estrictamente videojueguil, con algo más de interacción, exploración y resolución de puzzles hubiese bastado, pero acá no hay nada de eso. En este punto me encuentro en la disyuntiva de recomendar o no esta obra y creo que la recomendaré a quienes busquen pasar un rato agradable visionando una breve historia con un despliegue visual que estremece. Si buscas un juego de verdad, desafortunadamente deberás mirar hacia otro lado.", "appid": "203810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034558991", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0} {"text": "good practice for a real apocalypse", "appid": "368360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127694601", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561723200.0} {"text": "Bardzo fajna gra!! POLECAM WSZYSTKIM!! <3", "appid": "508900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198274142859", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1526558400.0} {"text": "It's ok. I don't really like the new expansion but meh.", "appid": "1085660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073982622", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "Классная игра, с друзьями топ играть", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198859018503", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588680000.0} {"text": ":* ...", "appid": "207610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198289501526", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542888000.0} {"text": "The Game is very similar to the first Layers of Fear but it has some changes like the story is better and longer than in the first game, its less scarier than the first game (i was carefull about the jump scares because of the first one) about the grafix.....the game has better grafix than the first game but at one point of the game the wole szene is grey you have really no colours. but i really liked the game and stuff and how the wole game is on a ship and how the place is changeing when you play the game more and more and i like too how the game is based on to find the character or better him/her self, after i played the game i felt better in life, i was thinking about who i really am. its very worth to buy the game and its really fun. btw sorry for my bad english spelling (the first game ---on top there lol uwu)", "appid": "1029890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198349510654", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559390400.0} {"text": "çok güzel oyunDU ya ben çok oynadığımdan yada başka bişeyden eski tadı kalmadı bu efsane oyunda yavaş yavaş yavaş ölüyo yeni bi cs oyunu beklemeye geçtim şahsen.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198277104836", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515931200.0} {"text": "My favourite anime characters move in the background. Do you have any questions? :P", "appid": "431960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198140403775", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "✅ Great multiplayer system: Ping can be high but the gameplay and connection is always smooth and steady. ✅ Great audio and visuals: The weapons sound very nice to fire and the game looks good but not so good that it’s unplayable. ✅ Incredible amounts of content especially for a multiplayer game, different armies maps and customization options. ✅ Good map atmosphere will make you feel like you’re in the conflict zone without overdoing detail or extensive color grading. ❌ if your network is slow or the drive on which you have this game is installed getting an in-game role or class you want is very challenging. ❌ Team balancing is virtually nonexistent and in almost every single scenario the winning team in one round will keep the upper hand. There are a lot of things that go into making a good multiplayer first-person shooter. It is important to make sure that not only the gameplay is entertaining but that networking isn't done poorly which will have your opponents teleporting all over the place. On top of that development team has to uphold the reputation of the previous installments in this series. Certainly a daunting challenge but in my opinion, it has been done exquisitely, only a few small problems exist that are not detrimental to the experience. RS2 is a multiplayer game, its core gameplay consists of a few game modes. While they are all different they revolve around the same premise: Capture point x until victory. This type of gameplay, while simple is a lot more engaging than simple deathmatch or free-for-all game-modes, it involves strategy and team coordination which is something that simplistic shooters cannot benefit from. To achieve these goals you work in a common way of organizing players in semi-realistic shooter games: Squads. All the players are divided into 6 man squads which then all answer to the game commander. An advantage this game has over others with similar structures is that, while it’s very useful, using your microphone to play is not required nor will anyone tell you to do so. A design step various games with similar core components take is to make sure you understand as little of what is going on as possible, this is done by not showing important or useful HUD (Heads-up-display) elements or by making them about as hard to use as Linux. RS2, however, doesn’t do this and gives you all the information you could want making the game not only useful to play but pretty when you need to, a lot of information can be hidden by a single button press. The visuals have gotten quite an upgrade since 2013 luckily however they have not overdone it like some other newer titles like “Hell let Loose” or “Post Scriptum” have done where your PC needs to have quite decent specs to begin with to make it consistently playable. Instead, this game, while not as pretty as the aforementioned titles, plays very nicely and consistently. The visuals look good enough to not be bothersome and provide clarity to properly engage in gameplay. The sound design is exquisite, the weapons stay authentic to how the real-life version sounds but they feel as good to fire as a weapon from ‘Call of Duty’ Firing the guns doesn’t get boring or repetitive which many other games suffer from, firing something that sounds like an auto-cannon takes a lot longer to get repetitive than a gun which sounds like a peashooter at best. I have caught myself picking certain guns more just because of the sound they make when fired, the combination with other sounds make the gunplay very enjoyable. A criticism I do have is that only your gun sounds like it packs a punch, even when standing next to an ally their gun still sounds like a box of paperclips being shaken around. Feeling the punch behind all of the guns would be better. When making a game in a historical period the history of the conflict you’re basing your game in is important. A good choice the developers made was to use history however to not be influenced by it. The maps, weapons, and vehicles follow the history but they are not limited by it. You can name quite a few historical inaccuracies for example that the Vietcong did not engage in open battle as much. However, this is not important since the focus is on producing a game that’s actually fun to play and properly works instead of one you can use to study for a history test. RS2 has 2 major problems, the first is that getting roles which only a few players can use on the team is quite difficult if you do not have it installed on a very fast hard drive or SSD. It’s a first come first serve system where the players that load the fastest can pick the roles they want before many of the other players have loaded forcing other users to take standard roles. While this works quite well for players with more higher-end PC's it ends up that with an average computer you will have to fight at the beginning of the round to get a role you want and just hope you are first, I find this to be flawed at best. The second issue is that team balancing is practically non-existent. If you join the losing team you’re going to lose the current and the next round as the teams are not auto balanced. I can understand this to an extent since you pick your team however nothing is done to give the losing team a hand so winning or losing depends on which team you pick upon joining a server which I think is relatively flawed but it’s not game-breaking. Surprisingly RS2 only costs 23 euros, that’s not a lot for such a large scale game when 30 euros would have also been an acceptable price. You’re essentially getting more bang for your buck then almost any other multiplayer shooter can offer you and the minimum requirements are quite low. So I would definitely recommend picking it up if you have the money to spend on it and well with a price this low most people do. RS2 has quite low system requirements so a vast majority of computers can run it and it will look comparable enough to higher-end systems. I was able to run on a mix of high to ultra on my computer : [GTX 1050TI OC, 16GB DDR4, I5-7600K] and I have noticed frame drops only once which was because of the server I was playing on. The multiplayer experience is great, even when your ping is high it’s hardly noticeable so only extremely high latency is a problem. Rising Storm 2 is a well-designed and well-executed game that not only provides you with a lot of playtime but with an enjoyable experience with great audio, functional visuals, and smooth multiplayer capabilities. All in all combined with a large amount of content, especially for a multiplayer game, it offers and the very low price for a game of this caliber I can do nothing but firmly recommend it. This game was provided for free by the developers.", "appid": "418460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138290285", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569672000.0} {"text": "Bardzo lubię Hotline Miami, zarówno jedynkę jak i dwójkę. Fabuła i \"stylówa\" na stare gry, jest jak najbardziej na plus. Co do tej odsłony - oto krótka list plusów i minusów: +Wpadający w ucho soundtrack, pasujący do rozgrywki. Mogłabym zaryzykować stwierdzenie, że lepszy od tego z jedynki. +Sceneria (lokacje są ciekawsze) -Postacie mają nowe umiejętności i jest ich sporo, ale tylko niektóre są grywalne.", "appid": "274170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198255191086", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487851200.0} {"text": "Ist gut kann man gut spielen!!!", "appid": "326460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198302912741", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1523016000.0} {"text": "sex", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998944560", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1511697600.0} {"text": "can't kill the floor", "appid": "232090", "steamid": "profiles/76561