o play either alone or even with friends! Perfect to just sit back and relax while building your own farm and such. Kinda reminds me of a mix of Starbound and Harvest Moon! For everyone who loves those pixel games a big must~", "appid": "413150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198257087441", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580731200.0} {"text": "Muy buen Juego :D", "appid": "588430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198344773621", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498564800.0} {"text": "Ну шо ни чё так игра", "appid": "321360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198142893364", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1499256000.0} {"text": "Могу отметить несколько плюсов 1.Карты от игроков(Некоторые очень интересные) 2 .Внутриигровой создатель карт 3.Еще несколько режимов(Обычный,арена,и что то вроде сюжета,даже мультиплеер есть) Что могу сказать сам: Игру стоит покупать если невчего играть или просто надоело играть в онлайн игры В общем игра отличная", "appid": "337320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198835123376", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1585915200.0} {"text": "very nice", "appid": "413150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198259998379", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594900800.0} {"text": "Strife® Это замечательная игра! Плюсы: +графика +множество героев +более-менее адекватные игроки! Минусы: -долгий поиск -очень похожа на Dota 2 Впрочем МОЯ оценка: 7.0/10.00", "appid": "339280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198134614322", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1438862400.0} {"text": "güzel oyun", "appid": "477160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198908675452", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590753600.0} {"text": "Ваше общение с этой игрой: 1) Увидели 2) Удалили Intetnet explorer, что бы места хватило 3) Скачали 4) Поиграли 5) Набили 2 новобранца 6) Пошли в мм 7) Выучили польский, что бы поставить тиммейтов на место 8) Получили по лицу от читеров 9) Ограбили 2 банка, купили прайм 10) Зашли 11) Откалибровались на сильвера 12) Впали в годовую депрессию 13) Пересмотрели все гайды 14) Апнули 2 сильвера 15) Радостные пошли на aim botz 16) Поубивали ботов, подняли самооценку 17) Пошли на аимку разваливать кабины, но получили по лицу 18) Поняли, что аимка не для вас и они вообще там все читеры 19) Пошли в мм, слили ранг 20) Спустя 2 года апнули нову МЫ ГОЛД НОВЫ ПРОСТЫЕ ПАЦАНЫ, ЗАШЛИ НА СЕРВЕР ПОЛУЧИЛИ ПО ЛИЦУ И УШЛИ!", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198445429367", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1534766400.0} {"text": "was....a lot of fun. In fact, I found myself chuckling throughout, when I wasn't outright laughing, with some interludes for fierce swearing at the screen. I've actually owned this for a while, but never got around to playing it until just recently. I kind of regret that. I know the player base was much higher in its heyday, and co-op is definitely the way to go if that is available to you. However, I would say I played about half the maps solo, and I had a lot of fun with that as well. So, YMMV in that regard. You play as one of four (with the base game anyway) members of the Strange Brigade, a sort of paramilitary/paranormal investigator/Indiana Jones style group, dedicated to finding ancient relics, new magic, and fighting evil along the way, and in the most cocksure fashion lol. The characters are all pretty awesome. They're also all hilarious, irreverent, and generally arrogant as well lol. There is a lot of interaction between characters, and the cutscenes always feature fun dialogue. On top of that, they have their version of Charlie or M, a mysterious lady who sends them on their missions. But that's not all. There is also narration, and the narrator interacts with whatever is going on at the time. For me, that was so much fun and was so hilarious. Very much in line with what you get from a game like The Stanley Parable in that regard, but with some James Lipton sprinkled in. Very over the top, almost safari documentary style narration. The main story features the Strange Brigade trying to stop an ancient demon from destroying the world. In a nutshell. There is also a lot of meta mixed in. The gameplay is consistent with what you would expect from a game like the Left 4 Deads, Vermintides, etc....the actual gunplay is very consistent with other Rebellion games. There is a small variety of different rifles, shotguns, and pistols. You will carry a pistol and one of the two others. You can also upgrade the guns with a variety of elemental damage, stat boosts and such. Additionally, you have a magic amulet with you at all times, with one of four ability options unique to your specific character. You will eventually unlock all four, but you can only take one with you. Level design is also what you expect. Some exploration, lots of waves of enemies, some loot, and so on. Some were better than others of course, but all were fun. There was a decent array of enemies as well based on the region, and bosses were pretty fun. Some were more like puzzles whereas others were straight combat. This game also features some tower defense elements, which comes into play when you're in the middle of one of the arena fights in this games. You'll be able to use obstacles and hazards against the waves of enemies...as long as your aim is true lol. Co-op is really the way this game is intended to be played, and it is a ton of fun whether with friends or randoms. However, as noted before, finding a co-op partner or partners can be problematic with the low player base. It's definitely possible, but i personally had to play about half the campaign solo. That said, it was also fun solo....just not AS fun as co-op. I appreciate that included the option though. The audio in Strange Brigade is masterful. The voice acting is all over the top, pulp style, with a heavy slant in the narration towards appearing to be a nature documentary lol. Each character has a lot of hilarious lines, and the narrator is good for constant chuckles and guffaws. The soundtrack is perfect for the game. All the in world sounds are great as well, and combat is completely on point. Visually, it is a nice mix of lush environments with cutscenes that feature cool, old newspaper clip/black and white silent film presentation (but without the silence lol). Very steampunk in that pulpy 1920s and 30s type of way. The in game graphics are some of the best Rebellion has offered so far. Lots of cool stuff to be seen for sure. Also, the way each new enemy and every boss is presented as you are first introduced to them or their new circumstances, is always awesome. Sooooo cool in a very noir sort of way. Strange Brigade is really a ton of fun, and it's really a shame that the player base has dwindled so much since launch, but even without the player base, this game is great.", "appid": "312670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044602606", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "27", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586692800.0} {"text": "Moba Sevenlerin Hepsi Oynamıştır Bu Oyunu Zaten :D , Zaten Smite,Lol,Hon'dan Başka Moba Yok :) +Grafik Lole Göre Daha Güzel +Seslendirme +Karakterler Hepsini Ücretsizdir. +Modellemeler +Karakter Çeşitliği +İtem Çeşitliği (İtemler Oyuna Pek Etkisi Yoktur Maçtan Sonra İtem Düşüyor Bazen) -Ruslar +Oyun İçinde Bazen Sabah Akşam Olması Güzel Bir Detay 10/9", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116704367", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1434888000.0} {"text": ".", "appid": "285920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198157886630", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591444800.0} {"text": "yes", "appid": "210970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198005313980", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601467200.0} {"text": "Realy good game 9/10", "appid": "22370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198157722896", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1439553600.0} {"text": "Excelente", "appid": "617670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130569421", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574769600.0} {"text": "- Pero miren quién es, el juego que decidió ver la luz del sol una vez más, después de... Bueno, creo que ya todos conocen la historia del 2016. No Man´s Sky es un claro ejemplo de un título que decidió volver a la vida, con un comienzo bastante desalentador. A pesar de su oscuro pasado, ha mejorado, y lo digo en serio, ha cambiado muchísmimo. - Han añadido modo historia, el cual está bastante bien, pero abusa demasiado del texto y no usa cinemáticas. La exploración planetaria es única, con fauna y flora variada, tormentas intuitivas y demás peligros bien construidos. Han añadido vehículos curiosos, bases peculiares y demás historias que hacen de No Man´s Sky un gran título. - Lo que parecía convertirse en un gran añadido al juego, terminó por ser una mera utilidad mal implementada, con bugs muy graves y un sistema de guardado patético que hace que aparezcas en medio de la nada en vez de donde realmente lo dejaste. Hay graves problemas de conexión y en general es muy inestable. Terminó por convertirse en una funcionalidad que ignoré a lo largo de mi experiencia. Si te gustó el análisis puedes darle me gusta y", "appid": "275850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198089811835", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533470400.0} {"text": "I played in turn with my girl) a ridiculous, smart game!) it is a pity that levels aren't enough as it seemed to us... there was a wish to play more and more)))", "appid": "447890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030138996", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495022400.0} {"text": "Всё ахуенно", "appid": "386180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198294132128", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1502539200.0} {"text": "fun and awesome game its hard to top playing once you start cant wait too see what is added in the future", "appid": "233450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149460052", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1436270400.0} {"text": "благодаря игрули дачу построил с банькой)))", "appid": "238320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198122948865", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487937600.0} {"text": "goooood", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083627562", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "nice", "appid": "113400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040208340", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0} {"text": "Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a sequel to the successful, though not perfect, shooter Kane & Lynch: Dead Men. She showed in full parade that there is no need to put a handsome positive in the lead role, because neither Kane nor Lynch are exactly handsome and not exemplary guys at all. You might think that after the first episode, our criminal duo Kane and Lynch will take a break from drug dealers, guns and criminals. Unfortunately, this did not happen and the very big crazy Lynch, around whom the whole story of the second part revolves, will go to Shanghai. We will soon find out that he did not come only on holiday when he plans a very risky event, in which, of course, there is money, drugs, weapons and local mobsters. Before the event, he had a good fight with his colleague Kan, but when he promises to help him a few million, from which he could sponsor his daughter, Kane nods and he is already flying to Shanghai too. However, Lynch is not exactly the type to think about, so his planned event has several large and small cracks, which will immediately manifest themselves. Thanks to this, our duo will become game not only for mobsters, but also for the local police. As you may already know, the main prime here will be the shootouts, which will take place in a total of ten levels. Unfortunately, this is not a large number, and believe me, the game took us about four hours of game time to complete the first game. This is a shame for the game like thunder. As for the gameplay itself, Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a classic action shooter that takes inspiration from American action movies. Quite simply. You go through all 10 levels, but they are as linear as possible, with crowds of armed enemies. Your only task is to get through them at the end. At first, only similar bastards will keep you company, but later the police and in the second half of the game also special units that have bulletproof vests, but also better submachine guns. In order for you to succeed in the shootouts, the developers have added to the game even so popular today, which is really successful in the second part of Kane & Lynch. Your end is also very interesting. If you refuse to cover and you simply want to shoot the level, after a few hits, the character you control goes to the ground, while he has the opportunity to shoot everything from the ground, or quickly get up and run to safety. Anyway, if you don't get out of range of the bullets, you'll end up in a pool of blood soon. Thanks to the considerable linearity and constant skirmishes, the game has a really fast pace and you will really relax when you finish the game. Even thanks to the brutal pace, the game will definitely not let you go. Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a hilarious action game that includes crazy shootouts full of violence and foul language. But in order to give a better mark, the game would have to be a bit longer, because less than four hours for the main campaign, that's a hell of a lot. Also, the game contains a fun Arcade mode and even the multiplayer is definitely not bad. But now the answer to the question of whether to buy or not. If you fell in love with the first part or you like purebred shooters, then definitely buy it. I personally rate the game 5/10 Positive + Literally a rough game + Cooperation mode + Multiplayer Negative - Extremely short campaign - Too stereotypical - A simple story", "appid": "28000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041153724", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601121600.0} {"text": "Press F and Let`s play", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198965902710", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1568203200.0} {"text": "Não vou mentir. O jogo é bom. Pulei todo o hype e todos os \"first day review\" e joguei. Me diverti demais, então recomendo. Embora seja muito caro pelo que oferece", "appid": "314710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079289820", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591444800.0} {"text": "Jogo muito bom, recomendo!", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198133277825", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493208000.0} {"text": "Bu oyun çok güzel ama keşke valve bey bi çözüm bulsa hilelere", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198860657124", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542628800.0} {"text": "this is the excitement with the amazing graphics and battle people a snapshot of how i write multiplayer i can write that you don't miss a game like this there are a few sections that all of them, the arena is going in there, you can improve your own character by cutting down on the enemy, whatever it be armor or a sword is upgrade completely up to you this game is when you should get a discount are you seen rome war", "appid": "302510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198180670294", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1491825600.0} {"text": "Awesome Game. Buy it now if you can accept that things aren't going to be perfect. If not i suggest waiting until the full release.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046418187", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1387281600.0} {"text": "<3 LOVE THIS GAME <3", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198313981983", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511006400.0} {"text": "When Metal Gear Survive was first revealed in 2016 I was left with mixed feelings. While I was never onboard the hate train I was not very excited either. Then once the first footage of gameplay was revealed the month after it was starting to look more appealing to me. At E3 2017 private showcasings were held for the upcoming spinoff and Konami invited me to attend the event. Once I was able to try out the game for myself I had a really good time with it and knew for sure I would be playing it at release. Much like The Phantom Pain Metal Gear Survive's main focus is on gameplay rather than story. The story content is a bit short and is heavily consisted towards the beginning and towards the end. The game begins with multiple cutscenes at the MSF motherbase where you also create your character between scenes. After creating your character it shows you how you end up getting sent through a wormhole to another dimension. You must use the resources you find on missions to survive in the harsh environment and find your way back home. Survive consists of many good plot twists while maintaining the Metal Gear feel. Building off of MGSV's core gameplay Metal Gear Survive adds many new mechanics and assets. Added assets include a variety of melee weapons, gear, apparel, and gadgets. In this game you must gather food and water to survive which can be tedious in the beginning of the game. However as you progress through the story it gets easier and easier as you build up your base. Eventually you will reach the point where you never have to hunt for food and water ever again. While the maps reuse assets such as textures and some buildings it still felt like a new environment to explore. On a final note stealth IS relevant in this game. If you sneak behind Detonators to kill them you get more materials and it prevents Bombers from blowing up and causing potential damage to nearby fortifications. I found microtransactions in Metal Gear Survive to be less intrusive than TPP's. The premium currency is called SV coins which are very similar to MB coins in TPP and can be acquired for free from the daily reward. You can use SV coins to buy temporary resource boosters, extra loadout slots, extra emotes, additional storehouse storage, and additional avatar slots. When you buy an avatar slot your resources such as weapons and materials are shared between your characters. If you were to delete your original character your resources would also still remain from your previous character which makes these avatar slots not truly save slots. In TPP you were locked out of the top equipment if you didn't buy extra FOBs with MB coins which is something Survive does NOT do. In Survive you can acquire all the top gear without using any SV coins at all. Metal Gear Survive is far from being the best Metal Gear game but I think it's the most enjoyable Metal Gear spinoff and offers more content than Metal Gear Rising ever did. I recommend this game to those who are craving for more Metal Gear content and looking to have a good time with friends. There is even still more to look forward to with a new CO-OP mode arriving in an update this month.", "appid": "543900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057945441", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "113", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520078400.0} {"text": "Играл в первую часть,понравилось.По демке нельзя многого судить,но,судя по ней,в игре еще больше взаимодействия с окружением,черный юмор на еще более высоком уровне) Стелс остался на том же высоком уровне,как и в прошлой части.ИИ немного туповатые,могут вас не увидеть,в метре от себя. Спокойно пойдет на компах 5-летней давности. Из минусов,так это цена-2к платить многова-то,брать ТОЛЬКО на распродажах,к тому же,как раз сейчас скидочка 50 % .", "appid": "630880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198099371283", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1502020800.0} {"text": "atla öl :)", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198361382397", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562241600.0} {"text": "Не знаю как там с мультиплеером - не любитель игры по сети, разве что в Гвинт наиграл под 700 наверно часов пока он был в бете как эксклюзив ГОГ, но Respawn сделали офигенный сюжетный боевик в рамках кампании Титанфолл 2. Простой но рабочий сюжет.Отличные паркур элементы, заставляющие страдать в уголке жалкие потуги из Doom Eternal на платформенные вставки в геймплей. Колоссальная насыщенность событиями, плотность действвия на экране в единицу времени зашкаливает, постоянно обыгрываются возможности героя и делается это разнообразно. Здесь и аренные бои на выживание, и постановочные ВАУ моменты с паркуром, \"танковые сражения\" в Титане аля Мехварриор, и классичские элементы из старых добрых коридорных шутанов. Научно-фантастическая атмосфера выдержана от и до - а совмещение игры со временем с мгновенным переключением между прошлым и будущим на одной из локаций прямо во время забегов с прыжками по стенам заставляет маркетинговый отдел ПС5 с ее мантрой \"такое можно только на ССД увидеть\" завалить хлебало наглухо и обтекать в стороночке - очень зрелищно и круто сделано. И главный + сюжетки это без сомнений шикарнейший напарник -Титан БТ-7274, проработкой с которым может поспорить разве что незабвенная Элизабет из Bioshock Infinite. Послевкусие такое - с Респаун можно идти в разведку и хочется толькол одного - чтобы ЕА доверили им какой угодно шутер от 1 лица в какой угодно вселенной - ребятки осилят.", "appid": "1237970", "steamid": "profiles/76561197987585729", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "49", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596196800.0} {"text": "Świetna zabawa na długie godziny. Fabularnie bardzo dobrze, oprawa audio wizualna również nie ma się czego wstydzić. Optymalizacja pozwala grać nawet na średniej klasy sprzęcie. Zdecydowanie polecam nie tylko fanom gier rpg.", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998518992", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479902400.0} {"text": "Top game, all advise", "appid": "799070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356483069", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542110400.0} {"text": "Me lo regalaron y está bueno el modo historia, el online ni lo toque porque seguro esta lleno de coreanos con autos al piso que te sacan 5 vueltas antes de que puedas meter segunda.", "appid": "44350", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054519364", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561118400.0} {"text": "Comparing to PS4, it was more easier to play on PC than I expected. It was fun but even funnier with skin mods haha", "appid": "883710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198833329234", "voted_up": true, "vo