17448249", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1473508800.0} {"text": "Je sais que c'est une alpha mais pour le moment je met un avais négatif : _Problème d'optimisation très clairement même en low c'est tendu du cul _Contrôle des voitures quasiment impossible _Impossible (pour ma part) de joué en multijoueur _Sa sert à rien de changé ces touches le jeu en a rien foutre _ect ect.. Je ne peux pas recommandé ce jeu dans sont état actuel, a voir aux prochaines maj.", "appid": "913780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113950995", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "23", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1565697600.0} {"text": "Worst piece of ♥♥♥♥ I´ve played so far. Matchmaking is full of little Kids, Smurfs and Hackers. Worst off all is if you got all three in one game what happens regularly.... I would not recommend this game to anyone until Valve does update their anticheat.... ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ ♥♥♥♥♥♥ game", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561197960329984", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1456228800.0} {"text": "IT ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ sucks", "appid": "322780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198236028752", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1531396800.0} {"text": "这世道有钱就是权，有钱就是能为所欲为。 开没开挂，心里没B数。 挂鱼不愧是大手子。 最后奉劝蓝洞赶紧把挂逼解决下，每天看到你的新闻（在线人数突破N万，同时游玩人数超过xxx), 看的烦。 好多主播为了吃鸡，和挂逼战斗，极限挑战，都快猝死了, 粉丝操碎了心，比关心自个的亲爹还亲。 Fix your game, take useful measures to handle the cheaters, OK? Feel shame with this FPS game, ironically, many people like to play with cheaters. Many live streamers fight with the cheaters just for the champion, day and night, nearly died, their fans' heat are already broken...", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198325039775", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1508328000.0} {"text": "I know I'll enjoy and play WWII when the official game is here. But as far as Open Beta is concerned, it's not good. The TTK is incredibly inconsistent. TTK is an issue in a lot of games, but it stands out more in this. The maps leave much to be desired. Moving around the menus and settings and even to exit the game is a soup sandwich. Matchmaking is, you guessed it, terrible. And right now, I can't even play the game anymore because of \"the game needs to restart due to an update error\". Again, I know this is Open Beta and not the real deal. With that said, it's a bag of a$$ in its current state. Edit: The \"update error\" is gone, so I can play again now. But since then I've had a couple crashes :/", "appid": "696790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002229482", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506686400.0} {"text": "Simplemente decepcionante. Mecánica y jugablemente pobre. Bastante repetitivo y poco emocionante. Tenía una buena base y concepto, pero terminó siendo algo bastante mediocre y desperdiciado. El precio es increíblemente exagerado para lo que realmente ofrece. Todo esto y muchas cosas más definen lo decepcionante que es Extinction. Era uno de los juegos que más esperaba este año y terminó siendo la decepción más grande.", "appid": "570710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198093444950", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1524139200.0} {"text": "хороший фарм с читерами я в шоке 1/10 и то за 7 рублей на халяву", "appid": "706990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198142607058", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1541505600.0} {"text": "es una basuraaaa >:v", "appid": "282660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198284950325", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520942400.0} {"text": "New game mod is ♥♥♥♥♥ as ♥♥♥♥", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198365752739", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545048000.0} {"text": "trash", "appid": "344760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019425076", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1469016000.0} {"text": "7月14日 凑3个人去QQ游戏大厅吧。 作为黄油，东西太少；作为打牌，队友太傻；作为价格，史低刚好。 7月30日 进群有半个多月了，刚发售的那几天最常见的就是群主说销量不好，评价不好。希望玩家修改评测。 但是请不要拿销量不好、评测好坏当作游戏质量不过关的借口，真正受到伤害的是真心喜欢这个游戏的玩家。我为游戏制作了欢乐斗地主语音替换包，也得到了各个群里上百次的下载，可见是有那么一部分玩家是喜欢斗地主才买的游戏。但是现在，我对游戏很灰心。对程序员敷衍了事的灰心。 第五关与偶像作为农民对战投资人地主，地主技能是华佗在世。官方29日发公告以及在个别评测中回复说技能bug已经修复。 也许是因为我语文不好看不懂技能介绍里的（按百分比向下取整，3级分别为3%5%7%）是什么意思，假设3%，5%，7%对应的是总血量。那么投资人2级技能95血对应每回合回复应为4.75血。 但是，实战中投资人依旧每回合回复14点血。95血在12回合内结束战斗，平均每回合约需打掉8血，加上回复的14点血，也就是除去最后一回合，平均每回合需要打掉22点血。可能单纯看这个数字很多人感觉不到什么，但是，当亲自打过一局之后，就不再需要更多的解释了。 而这个让玩家根本无法获胜的bug，已经存在1周并且在所谓的优化中依然无解。 再也不见，斗地主少女。 再也不见，这个我连名字都没记住的游戏厂商。", "appid": "1138080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198147840502", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594641600.0} {"text": "Legit paid for key revoked. You sold keys to a third party store and revoked them, and you will reap what comes from that.", "appid": "1420330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198326510209", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605009600.0} {"text": "This is a review for the \"Attack on Titan Mashup Set\" costume DLC for the game Dead o Alive 5. I won't make a big deal about how this version doesn't have the feature that costumes take battle damage like the PS4 version does. Most people point that out for reviews on every other DoA5 DLC page. The devs couldn't be ♥♥♥♥♥♥ to do it and for me it doesn't effect the game. It can't be helped. However this DLC reflects many things that are wrong with how the game and its fans are being treated. Lets look at the price first. Typically I think its dumb to make a big deal about the price for games or extra content as those will go down pretty fast via a sale or something just months later as is the current trend. However this DLC which was up for only a year never got a discount or sale. It remained the same price the entire one year it was available. You would think with the past Steam summer sale they might throw us a bone since they know it's going to be removed but nope. This leads us to the next thing to examine, the actual price. Here in the US it ran for $40. Putting that into perspective the game itself before turning over to the free to play model was either the same or lower the price depending on how you purchased it. Now I can't really comment on the amount of effort it took to make these costumes, yes they all look nice and accurate to the material they're supposed to represent but objectively they're just brown jackets with logos for a majority of the cast. Putting this also into perspective without making some arbitrary system of what takes more effort, I will say DLC costumes packs with more varied costumes cost less than this one did and they have also received discounts making them even cheaper than this. So where exactly does this price come from? Certain people at this game company trying to milk Dead or Alive and Attack on Titan fans for as much money as they can. Now to put the cherry on top in their fine print: \"*The Attack on Titan stage shown in the screenshots cannot be used in this version of the game.\" Well isn't that great? Just another reminder on how little they care about the PC community that they couldn't port over what was essentially a reskinned version of another stage already in the game. I think them having screenshots of content not actually in this game is also a violation, not sure if that new Steam rule applies retroactively. Seeing as how this DLC is getting removed though, I guess nothing can be done about that at this point. So for any devs wishing to make bank just know you need to have a crossover DLC with a hot property, mark it up for high of price as possible and then announce later that you're removing it so you get a surge more sales towards the end. So I guess my final rating is for the DLC itself: Brown Jacket/10 Rating for pricing and practice behind this: *You must have the latest update installed in order to view this rating.", "appid": "494510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021187733", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500292800.0} {"text": "Had to refund this mess. I simply couldn't enjoy it. Let's see why... It is literally a jack of all trades. \"What do you mean by that!?\" Simply that it has all of the aspects that make a great and immersive VR game....The problem is that those aspects are implemented extremely poorly. Let me give some examples: Melee combat: Raw Data VR specializes in this, and does it exceedingly well. If your draw to Skyrim VR was the potential for melee combat? Then I suggest Raw Data instead. It's a futuristic game, true, but the melee truly is astoundingly fun(albeit a bit motion sickening if you go overboard) Magic: A Mage's Tale specializes in this, and does it exceedingly well. If your draw to Skyrim VR was the potential for immersive magic, then I suggest A Mage's Tale instead. It's set in a 'similar' era as Skyrim, making it quite enjoyable as an alternative with truly exceptional controls, compared to the very uninspired nonsense that you'll find here. Archery: In Death specializes in this, and does it exceedingly well. If your draw to Skyrim VR was the potential for becoming an expert marksman sniper, then I suggest In Death instead. It plays more like a 'crucible' game...getting from Point A to Point B without dying, and if you complete it, you get moved to the next difficulty level, and so on, until you die. It might sound simplistic, and shallow to some, but trust me, it is a source of several hours of truly fun gameplay. And best of all, the controls are easy on your motion sickness, if you have it, meaning you can play it safely for hours. Stealth: Unknightly specializes in this, and does it exceedingly well. If your draw to Skyrim VR was the potential for remaining undetected and killing quietly, then I suggest Unknightly instead. Long story short? Skyrim is demanding $60 for trying to fit all of the niche requirements for good VR games, into one, and doing it extremely poorly and with absolutely zero inspiration. Save your money, and pick 2-3 of the above preferences, and find a game that suits that need.", "appid": "611670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033807841", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547726400.0} {"text": "The worst game ever out there, how is this game even alive. HOW IS THIS APPROVED IN STEAM", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198321458083", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520683200.0} {"text": "Dredd vs Death is a short, dystopian fps where you go through the levels helping the citizens of mega city one until inevitablly you are sent somewhere else to help people and fight punks, cultists and undead until you eventually learn that 4 boss characters have escaped from prison and then you help the people where the boss characters went and beat the bosses, until you beat the final one, Death. The fps gameplay is mostly standard, you get to have 2 weapons maximum and you have to keep the pistol that all judges use. The judge pistol has several ammunition options such as explosive. flammble. and ricocheting options, but I found that they werent particularly useful or even detrimental; lighting people on fire didnt seem to do much damage and if they run towards you then you risk being burned. The high explosive mode doesn't have a huge radius for hitting enemies and most of the time its not worth the time required to change ammo from the normal ammunition. Additionally, on some levels you don’t get much of a refill on the judge pistol and usually have to rely on using an alternate weapon and these alternate pistol modes use your limited ammo faster. There is also some unneeded fluff such as a reputation system where reputation increases when you arrest people and help citizens not get killed and decreases when you attack friendly targets and people who have already surrendered to be arrested; but this only matters for ratings unless you have the lowest reputation by killing friendlies, then the game will cause a mission failure. At some times there were bugs such as me sniping off some enemies that were set to be killed by a script and that caused a mission failure. Something that can get annoying at times is that its not clear where your next objective is, but the gameplay is fairly passable fps gameplay once you get past the bugs. The music in the game wasn't particularly memorable to me, but the dystopian setting and various advertisements for dubious fictional future products added to the atmosphere of the game. Given the short length and dated graphics in this game, I wouldn’t go out of my way to pick this up, but it was in a bundle and I got my copy from trading so I figured why not. Unless you really love the Dredd universe no matter the implementation, there are better games for your money.", "appid": "3710", "steamid": "profiles/76561197989203587", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "23", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1432555200.0} {"text": "i hated it i wish i could remove it from my library", "appid": "347510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144799623", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1464609600.0} {"text": "Я даже объяснять не хочу почему игра вызывает только отрицательные эмоции и плохое впечатление, но если кратко, то миллион контроля в секунду и некоторые герои наносят мизерный урон, а некоторые ваншотят по несколько лиц сразу, крч дота конечно говно говна, но лучше бы уже в нее поиграл.", "appid": "386360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065843396", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570881600.0} {"text": "suck my ♥♥♥♥ epic store games ♥♥♥♥", "appid": "49520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198324744669", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554292800.0} {"text": "The game is dead at the moment, but their new update coming out in June might be the rise of BATTALION 1944. I hope it wasn't overhyped just like the game. Don't buy till reviews go up.", "appid": "489940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198336104946", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1526472000.0} {"text": "浪费时间的无厘头小游戏", "appid": "652980", "steamid": "profiles/76561198285760855", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1501243200.0} {"text": "After 2,500 hours I can honestly say that this game will provide you with exhaustion, weakness, and desire to sleep as well as send you straight to the treatment ward in a medical facility. One thing I don't understand how there are still people cheating in matchmaking for 8 years straight, I alone have invested enough money into CS:GO for a single freelance programmer to develop an anti-cheat system that actually works, but instead the developers of the game are too greedy to care.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049935328", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482062400.0} {"text": "Игра на которую забили разрабы", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090570626", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1473336000.0} {"text": "Game constantly sends the worst or new players to your team. You're trying but game and your noob teammates are stealing your time every time Let me tell you easily what it means noob, idiot and boosted. These are all attributes of random teammates in competitive play.", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198312726857", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0} {"text": "complete and utter garbage, dont even waste time on the free trial", "appid": "269710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198232991136", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537617600.0} {"text": "Everything about this game make me angry! at least let me skip the damn dialogues.", "appid": "619340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002976293", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1535889600.0} {"text": "bruh where's the content", "appid": "359320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049951304", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592654400.0} {"text": "Dead game", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198064914739", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479988800.0} {"text": "Почему в игре нет предупреждения о том, что она может вызвать эпилепсию? С такими яркими фиолетово-оранжево-едкими цветами во всём, кучи мельчишений на экране - глаза вообще могут вытечь... Местами вообще не понятно, что происходит на экране и где мой герой. Много ненужных никому мини игр и примитивных головоломок. В целом вся игра выглядит вторичным ненужным кусокм Г-а. За рисковку Жаб и врагов вообще тому кто это сделал надо гореть в аду.", "appid": "1244950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006325591", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "105", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598011200.0} {"text": "Fallout 76 is a game with a lot of potential and good ideas, ruined by bad design choices and greed. It is certainly better than it was at its release, but it still suffers from a lot of problems it had at the start and you can't fix those by simply adding NPCs with Wastelanders update. Plus it has one of most predatory monetization systems with Atomic Shop and Fallout 1st shouldn't exist. Sometimes it feels like developers just took Fallout 4 and dumped it into an online world without making any adjustments to it, that you need to make if you are making an online game instead of classic one. Good things: 1. Amazing world, my personal favourite wasteland to explore 2. (Wastelanders) Dialogue system and writing is great, humour is back, you can build your character with dialogue choices, supporting cast is interesting, with their own motivation and personalities 3. (Wastelanders) Great quest design, there are some new ideas here I never saw in Fallout before 4. Weapon and enemy variety is decent, there is a lot to choose from and shoot 5. Weapon modification and card system are both good imo, but I know some people that prefer old ways of leveling up 6. Community is suprisingly nice, I never met any griefers and everyone was friendly, plus you can create vendor stalls to trade with other players, cool feature 7. CAMP building is fun, but a lot of good stuff is locked behind Atomic Shop paywall. Neutral - Main storyline - I personally like it (expect for Rose's story), but I know a lot of people that don't, but I think that with Wastelanders update it is a lot better, since now you don't just listen to hours of holotapes, but there are some actual NPCs at key locations. Bad things - oh boy, there is a lot 1. Level scaling system - Enemies level scales according to highest level player that passed through location, so good luck if you are just starting out and be prepared to be blasted by level 60+ enemies anywhere you go, unless you server hop 2. Weapons you find are usually locked behind level requirements, so even if you explore or kill high level enemies, you can't use anything you find, that ruins exploration for me, because what's the point? 3. Combat - to me it feels clunky, animations get bugged, enemies shoot through walls, they are braindead with no AI, most of them use melee attacks, so you just run around and try not to get hit, which gets boring quickly, it is basically a worse version of Fallout 4 combat 4. Survival mechanics - I don't understand what is their point, hunger and thirst meter only make your inventory full of food and water, but there is always enough of both, so you never feel like you are in danger and I personally think they should be removed or optional 5. Stash managment - In a game that tries to me an MMO and makes you pick everything up and rewards you with tons of weapons, you have a stash limit of 800, which can be easily filled in few hours and then you are stuck doing inventory managment for half your playtime. Why not decrease weight of items or make stash unlimited? I know that it is possible, because you offer it to Fallout 1st subscribers. 6. Side quests and lack of things to do - there are like 5 or 6 side quest and other than doing main quest, you are stuck with boring daily quests, so there is not that much to do here, but you need to level up if you want to explore high level locations, so you either grind low level mobs or try to push through main storyline and run away from stronger enemies, since there is no way to beat them and I don't think either of these two options is fun. 7. Bugs - Well there are still tons of bugs and synchronization issues, but it is better than it was at start. But it is still not perfect and I don't think it will ever be. 8. Fallout 1st and Atomic Shop - ♥♥♥♥ both of these, a 15 dollars/month subscription service in a game that doesn't work, that basically fixes like half of its problems and offers features that should be in base game is a slap in the face of anyone who bought this game. Atomic Shop sucks aswell, skins are overpriced and anything pretty is locked behind its paywall. So overall I can't recommend Fallout 76 yet and unless developers fix its basic problems and publisher stop being greedy and gives us basic features that should be in game for free, instead of paying for them, then I don't think that Fallout 76 will ever get a redemption story like No Man's Sky. It has potential though. Anyway full review is here:", "appid": "1151340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044956970", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598702400.0} {"text": "Что-то нагло подавать такое дополнение за цену инди игры (отличной инди игры). Если взять и вырезать 50 % контента из дополнения Кровь и Вино (Ведьма 3), то примерно будет эта сумма, да и контент подходящий под нее. Жадненько. Спорю компенсируют бесплатным дополнениям для God Eater 3, думаю так и есть.", "appid": "774011", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052740874", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581336000.0} {"text": "A lot of people have said the same, but after over two 10 hours of play time the game just stops launching. It was fun until then, because now i can't refund the game and all the dlc i bought. 3/10", "appid": "863550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198950690419", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595678400.0} {"text": "핵이 너무 많다", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198275512182", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1504872000.0} {"text": "Очень непросто далось это решение. В игре отличная графика (даже без HD-текстур пака), интересный геймплей и некоторые механики. Боевка на любителя, к ней нужно принаровиться. Но всё портит слабый сюжет (про второстепенные квесты молчу даже) и бич игр с большим миром - беготня туда-сюда. Это реально достает уже часов через 15-20. Да, есть быстрое перемещение, но зачем тогда добавлять в раскачку навык верховой езды? Тем, кому н