reathtaking story game and don't mind a bit of hack n slash, try NieR:Automata", "appid": "319630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198332686449", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550923200.0} {"text": "Das schlechteste SPiel was ich seit langem gespielt habe jeder verfügbare server ist ♥♥♥♥ man hat keine chance etwas zu machen da man auf jedem server gespwankilled wird auch von der aufmachung her funktioniert einfach nix Fazig einfach nur schlecht", "appid": "304930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198336842871", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1526040000.0} {"text": "Why is this garbage even on Steam. Canyon Capers is a, \"is a retro style platform game brought right up to date, with tons of levels, modes, collectables and secrets.\" The levels are terrible and repetitive, the modes don't bring very much into the game, collectables are annoying, and the secrets are so... unsecret (for lack of a better term) they might as well have a giant sign saying, \"COME HERE, I'M A SECRET, BUT DON'T TELL ANYONE!\" Don't get me started on the \"artstyle\" It's a bunch of reused, terrible textures. When you put them next to each other it looks even worse. Platformers are suppose to have tight, cutting edge, controls. Or a least decent ones? CC has floaty, slow, and clunky controls which are most of the time to difficult to use and caused many pointless deaths. This game isn't fun. This game shouldn't be on Steam. It's a joke. Zero out of ten.", "appid": "275490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198086073133", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1422100800.0} {"text": "First off, let me say I have played L.A. Noire before on other platforms and absolutely loved it. It is truly a one of a kind game and if you own a console you should definitely play it. As for the PC version, it seems due to a series of updates to WIndows 10 that the game is broken now. In my experience, I would hit launch game on the menu and it would begin to load up, but then crash soon after that. I have tried all the different fixes I could find and none of them have worked for me, and as far as I know Rockstar isn't planning on fixing the issue completely anytime soon. I know some people have been able to fix the game, but unfortunately, I wasn't able to. If you are able to get this game to work, it is an unforgettable experience. Feel free to comment below if you have any fixes I may have missed, and if it works I will happily change this review.", "appid": "110800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198093830694", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533038400.0} {"text": ":(", "appid": "686810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034067963", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "Do not recommend buy this game yet. Potentially the game is very good: gameplay, mechanics, overall crafting/pve/pvp system. The flaws though are overwhelming at all the end-game sides. Some of them include: 1. Hackers. Game is full of hackers. Game has no hack protection system so anyone is free to use them. Ubisoft does not report if they are banned at all, there is nothing you can do except writing a mail to \"general\" section and get no reply. 2. Crafting materials that dont drop. You can spend up to 6 hours with no progress on your itemization/craft materials. 3. Weird game development that just jumps from one state to another in a blink of an eye, you cannot predict anything. If those things get fixed and we get BLUEPOSTS from company, then yea, game will be worth it. But NotLikeThis.", "appid": "365590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017440021", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1458993600.0} {"text": "2/10 nie polecam kappa", "appid":