pressive. You'll be lucky if it works half of the time. No theater / room options.", "appid": "755770", "steamid": "profiles/76561198309142266", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1582027200.0} {"text": "$5 normally.... 3.34 on current sale.... Doesnt add much for the price tag.... Legit wish i spent this money on some rolling papers or somethin", "appid": "512032", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049565274", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "23", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564142400.0} {"text": "Only play this game if you have no life.", "appid": "346900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198153581376", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1454241600.0} {"text": "Zamana meydan okuyan oyunlardan. Çıkışının üstünden tam on iki sene geçmiş olmasına rağmen halen yepyeni duruyor. Parkur mekanikleri keyifli, aksiyon sekansları heyecanlı. Ayrıca sürükleyici, bolca ters köşe yapan bir senaryoya sahip. Nitekim inceleme yazmanın bana göre temel amacı: Fiyat/Performans oranıdır. Ürünü mevcut durumuyla değerlendirir ve o fiyata değip değmeyeceğini analiz edersiniz. Mevcut durumu son derece başarılı. Oyunlara puan vermek huyum değildir ama rahatlıkla 8.5 puan alır benden. Lakin gelen son zamla oyunun fiyatı 31 liradan 129 liraya çıktı. On iki sene önce çıkmış bir oyuna zam yapmak, hele ki fiyatını dört katına çıkarmak nasıl bir kansızlıktır? Bu fiyata değil bu oyunu, ikinci oyunu olan Catalyst'i bile almam. Haliyle f/p yönünden kesinlikle önermiyor, sağlam bir indirime girdiğinde ise kaçırılmaması gerektiğini düşünüyorum :)", "appid": "17410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198188247685", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "38", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592827200.0} {"text": "Trash ass game dont play it even if you dont have a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ social life!", "appid": "537180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079917129", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563019200.0} {"text": "trash game", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198193584790", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1469275200.0} {"text": "small maps only spray and run no real weapon balance", "appid": "696790", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970285098", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506945600.0} {"text": "The game's been out for over a year, but is still performing very poorly. I had black lines appear in front of Bruce's mouth and nose, and Alfred's hair and eyes were floating aroung his face. Performance is poor at best, constantly stuttering framerate and lag on scene changes. Running on a 7970 w/ up to date drivers. Have uninstalled & reinstalled the game, verified the integrity of the game files, and searched for solutions on the internet and on Telltale's webiste. Still no difference. Even the title screen is bugged and laggy. After this amount of ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ I'd usually get a refund, but the game was apparently idling in the background for three hours without appearing on my task bar. I only realised this after I tried to boot up another game and Steam told me I already had one running. Only found out that it was running through task manager. This game performs worse on Medium settings than Witcher 3 does on Ultra. I'm very sad to have to give such a negative review as I am a long time fan of Telltale and have been looking forward to buying this and The Enemy Within, but this really is inexcusable.", "appid": "498240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061954400", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1502280000.0} {"text": "Almost Pay to Play. A waste of Harddrive space.", "appid": "349700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006359590", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1443268800.0} {"text": "Where to even begin... The cons and some comparisons to the original: They have sacrificed core mechanics of the game in favour of historical accuracy despite never being a historically accurate game in the first place. The native civs can no longer tame animals, which was one of their coolest features, and the North American natives can no longer mine and are required to construct an additional building to be able to acquire coin. Changing things in the game to be more accurate and considerate towards people who were presented in the game in a way that was ignorant or even disrespectful is fine, great even, such as changing the names of the civs to what they actually call themselves, but changing core mechanics and lazily introducing them is not. This is an absurd and unnecessary change that is an insult to veteran players. A major pet peeve of mine is the change from colonial era to commerce era. Are you trying to tell me that a game, that is built around the theme of colonialism, around the era of colonialism and who's entire gameplay is based around building a colony can't have the colonial era in it because it is too offensive. Was colonisation an awful thing for many people, YES, absolutely, but it happened and its what the game is based around, the game isn't making it out to be some glorious thing. This change of course does nothing to the actual gameplay so I'm not going to give up on the game just because of that but it is extremely idiotic and useless. Home city progression has been almost completely removed. You can still level up your home city, however, it only unlocks the customization options for the visual appearance of your home city and no longer unlocks shipment cards, as you now start with all of them. While this works great for multiplayer as you no longer have to grind of out matches to get the cards you need to stay competitive, it is awful for singleplayer. There is no more sense of progress or goals to work towards and the main replayability of singleplayer is simply gone. This is the change that makes me just not want to play the game, I used to love unlocking and experimenting with different makeshift shipment decks as I worked my way up to the more powerful ones, but that is no more. The UI is a complete and utter joke. The visual design of it looks as though someone made a bunch of text boxes in Microsoft Word and copied and pasted them onto the edges of the screen. The original AoE 3 had a UI design that was full of character and had amazing satisfying sounds to match. The definitive edition UI is completely soulless and had ear-piercing horrendous sounds mixed in with some rehashed sounds from the original version that somehow sound worse. To add on to this, the deck editing menu is nigh unusable, its essentially just a massive blob of the possible shipments you can use with very little sorting options. The original deck editor showed you what building the card type, what era you could get the shipments in and the progression trees all at the same time, allowing for easy location and identification of each card. In the definitive deck editor you can sort by age or by card type thats it, enjoy, and the cards are in a seemingly random order with no visual separation making it a long unsorted messy list of shipments that fit said categories. This only what I've discovered and thought worthy of mentioning in my mere 2 hours of playing the game. I've hear many other people mention how poorly optimized the game is but I have had no issues with performance as of yet, so be cautious in checking if your pc can actually run the game. The pros: The two new civs seem unique and interesting, haven't played with them enough to say for certain but I'm not really picky with how strong or standout they are, just happy to have new content. The graphics are a decent upgrade, nothing ground breaking but they generally look nice. Having achievements is nice, there aren't a lot of them but something is better than nothing at this point. It's cheaper than the original AoE 3, which is nice. yeah, that's about it, it's a ♥♥♥♥ show. The Meh: The sound revamps are overall higher quality and are likely more accurate but they take away a lot of the nostalgia of the original and are also a lot less satisfying (in my opinion). The long list of changes to the native civs are great for recognising and respecting these cultures and for the most part don't really affect gameplay, however they ruin a lot of the games nostalgia (which is admittedly a sacrifice I think we can make) and a lot of it is lazily done, such the community plaza, where villages walk in circles for some reason and it looks ridiculous. The fur trading building used to get coin is gathered by villagers as if they were plucking berries... from the side of a building... built next to a coin mine... which they aren't allowed to gather from... but the fur trade drains coin from the mine? Very historically accurate, thanks devs. It's just looks stupid and is clearly not very thought out, but once again, doesn't affect gameplay so it's not that big of a deal. Things they could change to make this better: Major problems: A big one would be to revert the any and all mechanic gameplay changes (not balance changes). I can understand if they don't want to do this because they have committed to it and don't want to insult the very people they changed it for. Add the option to have level unlocked shipments and restore the progression mechanics in singleplayer Make the deck builder the way it was in the original or add more features to make it less of a nightmare Minor problems: Add the option to use legacy sound effects Allow for more in game UI customization Make the main menu UI less of steaming pile of ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ Summary I'm pissed off. I've played more hours of AoE 3 than can possibly be counted, accumulated over the span of over a decade and to see it's legacy end with this disappointing mess makes me extremely sad. I've been beyond hyped since the first Definitive Edition was announced as I was hoping that AoE 3 would get one, and I was even more hyped when AoE 3 was confirmed to get one. I am not hard to please when it comes to remakes, I would have been satisfied and given this game a positive review if it was simply a graphics upgrade with nothing else but they went ahead and made changes that no one wanted, removed content and sucked the soul, the character and the passion from the game, all in one fell swoop. Some additions after seeing the comments: People are thinking that I'm railing on the devs for giving in to offended people, I'm not, I'm fine that the changes to the names and appearances of the nations, buildings and other things make the game more inclusive. What I am not ok with is compromising the gameplay for the those reasons. It's likely my fault for giving off that impression as my paragraph on the whole colony renaming ordeal made it out to be a lot more serious than it really is. I don't want to hate the game, I don't want to see it fail, I want to enjoy it. In it's current state, however, I don't see myself playing much of it and I would love to see that changed.", "appid": "933110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198373502045", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "36", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602763200.0} {"text": "I can understand that this game looks appealing to anyone who is a fan of police games. Wether that be LSPDFR, Flashing Lights or any other police game/mod/simulator out there. And I truly wish that this game was good. But unfortunately it just isn't. There are far too many bugs for me to enjoy this game. The movement is pretty crap and the lack of content makes it frustrating. Usually I wait and see a few days before giving a review but considering the developers already stated that no more content will be added to the game, I have no hope that it will improve. A true shame. I waited almost a year for this game.", "appid": "461870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198068430953", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1560859200.0} {"text": "Stole my friend :(", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198145132664", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583668800.0} {"text": "ВЕРНИТЕ СТАРЫЙ РАСТ !!!", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072057854", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "61", "votes_funny": "13", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1434283200.0} {"text": "Game is okay. You die too quickly and i personally dont have time to react to someone shooting me. I like the healing system. Shields are a bit meh. Don't belong in the game. I only find the same 3 guns per match. I notice theres lots of weapons in the game tho, where are they?? The 'GAS' kills you incredibly quickly and there is no way to out run it. (this kills the game completely for me)", "appid": "506540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198268722545", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500811200.0} {"text": "preety bad", "appid": "291550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198248760896", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520424000.0} {"text": "1,99€ for a 5 minute ride isn't really worth it. you could get better and longer games for the same price.", "appid": "741490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198042896883", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605355200.0} {"text": "is the dictionary definition of \"Asset Flip.\" The experience is laughably short, comprised of just two 3-minute missions, has the most basic A.I. imaginable, and is inhabited by barely altered low poly models seen in far too many games already overpopulating Steam. I'm not even going to bother to do my usual Pro/Con breakdown, this isn't a game, it's barely even a tech demo. I'll give the developer credit that the first stage environment is visually interesting, but that's as far as it goes. The castle stage has a far more fun-looking town just north of your spawn point, but it's devoid of life, and no structures can be entered. Everything is window dressing to hide the fact that the game has zero substance. Enemies are dumb as a rock, capable of only the most basic attack. Apparently, if you hit several in close proximity, they will start to turn on each other until only one is left standing. Is this an intentional feature? Whatever the case, it trivializes the game's already anemic difficulty. Stage 2 has you climbing castle walls, but this mechanic only works when standing on giant \"climb\" buttons which vanish after use. Once you reach the holding cell of your fellow tribeswomen, the game abruptly ends. I'm not sure if there is a legitimate way to enter the cell other than from above... I kept swinging a sword until I clipped through the gate by accident. And finally, doesn't even deserve the Hentai in its title, obviously added for sales effect. Nudity in this game is equivalent to looking at a Barbie doll. What's the point of being able to toggle clothes in the first place when you can already see through their revealing leaf coverings? For collectors only. Consider this game at risk for removal, should Valve QC decide to start doing their job. : Extremely easy. Complete both stages, double click the nude option in the main menu. You're done in under 10 minutes if you don't explore.", "appid": "1248970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198219343843", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592308800.0} {"text": "Копатель в стиме ЯСН", "appid": "278970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198151074381", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1434024000.0} {"text": "DONT PLAY THIS ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ GAME, THERE ARE SPAMMERS EVERYWHERE, THIS BRAWHALLA COMMUNITY IS DYING BECAUSE THE SPAMMERS !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "appid": "291550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198414604005", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583582400.0} {"text": "Вот небольшой перечень мракобесия которые я встретил в этой помойке: 1 Графика - уровня hl1 (Я играл на gtx 750 ti на почти максимальных настройках графики) 2 Управление тут пиздец какое неудобное! Я быстрее научусь летать на вертолетах в ravenfield'e, чем научусь ходить НЕ как алкаш в этой недо-игре 3 Багов тут просто дохера, вот только пару из них: непрогрузка, рандомная смерть, миссхит в упор 4 Сложностью это сложно назвать, это просто долбежка в сраку - Вывод напрашивается сам на себя: юбисофт, верните мне те 10 часов моей жизни которые я потратил на скачивание этой помойки", "appid": "304390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198838552982", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538136000.0} {"text": "Empfehlenswert: Nein (persönliche Wertung: 0/10) Errungenschaften: Nein Positiv: - Große post-apokalyptische Open World - Individuelle Charaktergestaltung - Gutes Kampfsystem Negativ: - funktioniert nach 2 Stunden Spielzeit nicht mehr Fazit: Fallout 3 ist ein etwas älteres Spiel, welches in einer post-apokalyptischen Welt spielt. Wir beginnen in einem isolierten Vault, müssen jedoch von dort fliehen. Nachdem wir den Bunker verlassen haben, finden wir uns in einer großen Open World wieder und gehen zur nächsten Stadt. Dort kann man Handeln, Quatschen und Quests annehmen. Die Grafik ist annehmbar und der Sound auch. Die Welt quillt über von kleineren Details und die NPCs waren so misstrauisch mir gegenüber, wie in jedem typischen Rollenspiel. Innovativ ist das Kampfsystem, welches mir sehr gut gefiel. Warum dann eine schlechte Bewertung? Nun... Ich habe das Spiel 2 Stunden lang gespielt und danach konnte ich es nicht mehr starten. Neuinstallation und Patches haben auch nichts gebracht. Schade, aber dadurch: Nicht Empfehlenswert!!!!", "appid": "22370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198064139415", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586433600.0} {"text": "死母亲的孤儿游戏 决战时候游戏报错 NICE 挂壁满天飞 NICE", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198101495296", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1507896000.0} {"text": "Pay to win muy obvio, si pagas y compras monedas eres el mejor del juego, tienes poderes y demas, lo mismo pasa con el MITOSIS. No lo recomiendo, casi mejor el SLITHER.IO Saludos :)", "appid": "466910", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961225211", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1566561600.0} {"text": "GG VALVE !!!", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198362862563", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545220800.0} {"text": "This game seems somewhat incomplete/buggy. Some of the doors do not open, no matter what you do. The slow and sluggish walk is just annoying. Not sure what these developers were thinking...it's like they spent a week on this and released it, didn't even bother to change the Unreal Engine titles. I wonder how games like this even get on steam? I highly do not reccommend this game. Even for being free it is a waste of your time to even download, and a waste of your storage space. There are plently of better, free games out there.", "appid": "824880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118889711", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523275200.0} {"text": "Говно а не игра для дебилов дебильных", "appid": "700330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198820281381", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537704000.0} {"text": "cant find a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ server", "appid": "707010", "steamid": "profiles/76561199032855562", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1597665600.0} {"text": "Very boring and slow game. Don't know what the hype is all about. UI is very clunky and messy and absolutely unappealing to look at.", "appid": "1147690", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998768135", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591358400.0} {"text": "帧数就没上过10，其他游戏都是稳稳的60，不是很懂", "appid": "241560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120619094", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1521460800.0} {"text": "Кривое управление, стрельба не чувствуется, отсутствие разрушаемости и физики. Минусов много! Да и еще микротранзакции. Это г_авн_о е_ban_oe снова!", "appid": "337000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198058519876", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1472126400.0} {"text": "--- --- +Has fantastic potential with the home base and possible customization +Good graphics +Well polished considering how far into development it is --- --- +Super long queues with no bots to fill in so games generally have 2-4 players at a time +Paid game with in game purchases (cosmetic only) +Very limited current customization options --- --- RAMS is a Battle Royale game with a twist. You start with a fully fledged base of operations! With good graphics and RPG elements, RAMS has a TON of potential. --- --- : Pretty straight forward, it's hard to mess with an fps set up. Still, the hand to hand combat seems to be a bit funky with hits not landing when they should and some hits landing when they shouldn't. : The player starts the match on a train moving through the landscape where most battle royale's will have you in the air, giving you a more 3 dimensional approach to your original spawn, where the train is a 2 dimensional, leaving it easy for players to see when another player gets off the train and able to hunt them down quickly. Furthermore, you start matches with weapons, which, once again, wouldn't be a problem if the spawn system was a bit different. In it's current state, it's too easy to hop off the train right after someone else and gank other players making the already short games far shorter when there's only two people. : Pretty solid. After the match is done you get a good amount of money so you can buy more weapons and ammo. I'm sure eventually customization options will allow you to buy cosmetics for your base. --- --- : Good graphics. I haven't seen much of the environment because of previously mentioned spawn camping and games with only 2-4 players. : Basic, however it seems that in the future there will be customization, but as of right now there's nothing special to note, good or bad. : Crouching is too fast and feels unnatural, when you jump your arms stretch straight in front of you, other than that everything seems a bit clunky but otherwise fine. : Straight forward, your general fps interface in matches but what I really like is how your home base acts as the main menu with a straight forward 'e' to activate and 'alt' to allow cursor to select menus. --- --- : The only bug I saw was while waiting in the lobby for a game random player models would kind of pop in on the spawn point. Nothing that breaks the game as far as I saw. : Solid performance, no lag on my end. However, without a full match of players to test the performance of the game you'll have to take this with a grain of salt. --- --- : Has potential in the future if the devs can attract a larger player base. : I would certainly not be happy paying 12$ for this. I frown upon non free to play games that have any sort of system where you can buy in game currency. On top of that, the game is currently unable to be completely experienced without the ability to play a full match. The dev's should honestly think of making this a free to play title and have more in game items to purchase such as early development donation skins for weapons and players. --- --- There's a base of a game here, but no real gameplay in sight. No one is going to pay for this in it's current state if they see the reviews first. There's no one playing and if you get lucky enough to get into a match or two, it's only going to be against a couple players. However, if the devs take my advice and make the game free to play with in game purchases, I feel that the player base would grow quickly and make the game a bit more worth playing. Until then, I feel that this game is will not succeed on the current market, it simply doesn't have enough to offer that other, popular games already offer for free. In case the devs do take my advice and make this free to play, giving those that purchased it some sort of compensation, I'll keep this game on my radar and re-review it in the future. Keep up the good work guys, this game has a lot of potential and I'm excited to see where it goes. --- --- \t\tCPU \t\t\tIntel Core i5 @ 3.60GHz \t\tRAM \t\t\t16.0GB Dual-Channel Unknown @ 1066MHz (15-15-15-36) \t\tGraphics \t\t\t4095MB NVIDIA GeForce GTX 970 (EVGA) I recieved the game for free for review purposes", "appid": "809580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198000526549", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1537704000.0} {"text": "game not working betch มันไม่เคยโหลดสำหรับฉัน ? ฉันใช้เวลามากและยังไม่ดี error error i get on game ฉันต้องการเงินคืน ! money i want back ! idiot ฉันโกรธในขณะนี้ , เกมนี้เป็นความผิดหวังที่ยิ่งใหญ่", "appid": "357480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198123388336", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "35", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1469966400.0} {"text": "i LIKE COOKIES NOT ZOMBIEZ :(", "appid": "304930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198094424495", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1420891200.0} {"text": "E' difficile che io recensisca così negativamente un gioco da non consigliarne l'acquisto, però pubblicizzarlo come uno dei migliori giochi in cooperativa dell'anno e poi scoprire pochi giorni prima del rilascio che manca un sistema di multigiocatore online è davvero assurdo. In un gioco del genere non dovrebbe mancare un sistema di lobby per giocare online con gli amici. Consiglio l'acquisto se ci si accontenta del multigiocatore locale e del giocatore singolo, dato anche che il gioco in se è molto carino. Fino ad un eventuale futuro aggiornamento la mia recensione rimarrà invariata.", "appid": "448510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009089148", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1470225600.0} {"text": "O jogo e louco demais divertido, te prende muito tempo, cada partida é uma mais doida que a outra. Mas infelizmente eu fui banido indevidamente, ja tinha alguns meses que eu não jogava, quando fui jogar pra ver o que tinha de novo, na minha primeira partida tomei BAN, sem explicação, ja mandei vários tickets para pubg, mas eles não da a minima, então eu vou procurar meus direitos de consumidor, é se possível abrir um processo judicial, de pequenas causas. sempre fui um jogador limpo, sempre personalizei meu perfil steam pra fica da hora, para tomar um banimento e perder o me