was going. This game could have been done better. Can't recommend it.", "appid": "817510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197977724919", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537099200.0} {"text": "Ding Ding Ding Motehr ♥♥♥....!!!", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198825925588", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571918400.0} {"text": "O jogo é divertido, porém TODA SEMANA tem atualização de pelo menos 1 giga. É ridículo.", "appid": "236110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017983015", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1477656000.0} {"text": "Pro : _ Great graphics, special effects and sound environnement. _ Boss battles are pretty cool. That's all. Cons : _This game is slow, which make the gameplay terrible : __ Your character is too slow. The \"light\" weight config in this game is the \"medium\" one in DS. You will fatroll a lot with the wrong equipement and config. So you will use shortcut to switch between armors and weapons while a combat to have something \"fair\" at the right moment. Amazing experience. __ On a controller, button registration are too slow. Be ready to die or take stupid damage cos the game didn't registered to dodge/parry/run at the right moment. Sometimes, it is just the mob which are broken because of bad coding. __ The camera is too slow, even with the higher sensibility and/or locked on an ennemy. Plus, the bad automatic view is horribly managed. It will make you killed against walls or in corridor because the camera will automatically choose a wrong angle where you will see nothing but a wall texture. Then, you ll lose time to center the camera on the combat. Amazing experience. _ Magic. Spells are simply OP. Almost at the third of the game, when you ll start to have a decent build, you will be able to face any situation with the strenght of thousands suns. Big damage, big range, pretty fast reload. Magic items are strong too. For example, one of them accelerate the mana regeneration and an other one give you a nice health regeneration. Lot of power. The thing is without magic or combat skills you can't do nothing, but if you mix both, you will be a semi-god. In endgame, you can rule only by magic effortlessly. _ No map, no second quest reminder. The level design is so poor than everything have the same taste. Except if you have good sense heading, you ll forget where things are. The big problem is that you need to come back a lot of time on already visited places for many reasons. You d better draw or take screenshot with notifications. _ Except bosses, combat is generic. Almost every mob have 2 kind of totally breakable attacks. Once you are used with (10 seconds, no more), you ll start rolling on ennemies because it is a really simple AI with really simple moves. I repeat, only the camera and slow gameplay will kill you. _ Bad key mapping, it is the same button to jump and roll. Prepare to roll in pits and jump in ennemy's attacks. To sum up, this game is only for the eyes and the ears, not much.", "appid": "265300", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998411882", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1508846400.0} {"text": "Good graphics and decent voice acting, but that is where it ends. The story is rather confusing. Tedious horrendous puzzles. Extremely boring walking simulator. Filler garbage combat. I literally cannot comprehend how this game gets so much praise.", "appid": "414340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198147883079", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581163200.0} {"text": "В место игры запускается Micrsoft Word, не удалось запустить игру ошибка, игра зависла и убили!", "appid": "550650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198184663303", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576065600.0} {"text": "It happened. Probably happened to you too. I got scammed. I haven't been scammed this bad since War Z. I bought into this game believing what the devs were saying. Believing that they would continue working on the game. Believing that they would fulfill their promises. I believed it when they said they aren't tied into the same War Z dev team and this isn't a scam. I was a fool. It's incredibly disappointing because I really wanted to enjoy this game. Nothing would make me happier than a Red Dead Redemption style MMO. A time period that isn't often captured in gaming but has so MUCH depth to it. I was lied to. I was scammed. Don't buy this game. For the record... the lead admin last logged into THEIR OWN forum August 16th. A month ago. He last posted in July. The devs have not answered any threads or replied to anyone on the Steam forums. This game should be pulled from the store.", "appid": "743860", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970322108", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "87", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537012800.0} {"text": "Sowas von tot. Letztes Jahr gabs noch Updates im 4 Monate Abständen. Nun gabs seit 8 Monaten nichts mehr. Mal davon abgesehen, dass sich des Game noch im \"Grundgerüst\" Modus befindet. Alles seeeeehr minimalistisch nd funktional... sofern es denn funktioniert.", "appid": "369080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198013036569", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1503403200.0} {"text": "I enjoyed this game better when it was downloading.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198172281185", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1474545600.0} {"text": "I had my eye on Chaosbane for some time as both a fan of Diablo-style ARPGs and Warhammer, but passed over it at launch and thereafter due to is very mixed reception. I heard about the upcoming added Witch Hunter class and was motivated to finally take the plunge. Having now tried it at a sale price, I can say it's not really my thing, and that is disappointing. I do like the game, but it didn't grab me like an ARPG ought to. By all means try it for yourself, especially if you have someone to try the local coop with. I expected a situation where the beginning gameplay would be entertaining and that if I stuck with it I would encounter the dearth of endgame content so often referred to in other reviews, but as you can see from my play time I obviously did not get that far. I cannot pinpoint what about Chaosbane turned me off other then the general slowness of the combat flow, but 40k Inquisitor also has this and that in of itself did not kill that game or this one for me. There is just something... off about Chaosbane's basic gameplay. It made me want to go play either Vermintide 2 or a different ARPG. Chaosbane seems competently designed, taking several mechanical cues from Diablo 3 that kept me playing that game for so long: recharging health potion, a range of AoE and movement skills, easily redistributed skill allocations, et cetera. The basics are there, but the X factor is not. It lacks the charm and mod support of Torchlight 2, the audio/visual flair and breakneck combat pace of Diablo 3 or the oomph and diverse character builds of Grim Dawn. I must say I am impressed that it has a local coop option, and that alone almost made me decide to keep the game, but it's hard getting even one other person to play these sorts of games with me. It wouldn't be the first time I enjoyed a game in coop that I didn't alone. I would be willing to try Chaosbane again somewhere down the line if I heard it made some improvements to its formula.", "appid": "774241", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970739339", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603972800.0} {"text": "ist scheiße es ist dauerhaft geöffnet und lässt sich nicht schließen", "appid": "442080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198162367721", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482494400.0} {"text": "Это фиаско братн", "appid": "696790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198218422576", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506600000.0} {"text": "绝地求生大道歉", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100526299", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1506513600.0} {"text": "Ce n'est parce que je ne mets pas du rouge que je recommande sans modération. J'ai hésité à mettre une recommandation ou non, désireux d'offrir à qui chercherait les raisons éventuelles de ne pas se laisser tenter par ce jeu les bonnes raisons de suivre son instinct méfiant. Puis, je me suis résigné, basant mon idée sur le fait que je reproche à This War of Mine la même chose que Dead in Bermuda, que j'avais gratifié d'un pouce bleu là où ma critique se faisait mitigée. Comprenons-nous, TWOM est un bon jeu d'ambiance et de concept. Suivre des civils faillibles dans un monde qui les dépasse est fort, comme l'était le destin des naufragés de Bermuda. Graphiquement sombre, déstautré, dépressif, c'est beau d'une poésie dystopique où vous serez en lutte constante contre le mauvais sort, tout surpris que vous serez de pouvoir accomplir de bonnes actions. Le hasard tiendra une part forte dans chaque partie, qu'on parle de la génération de zones aléatoires, de la visite de pilleurs ou non, de ce que vous trouverez lors des fouilles ou encore de ce que le commerçant occasionnel viendra vous proposer d'échanger. Un jeu prometteur, séduisant, bien réalisé, important à tester. Mais alors, où est le piège ? Ben le piège, c'est que TWOM est un jeu qui ne cesse de vous rappeler qu'il en est un. D'une main il vous vend une ambiance immersive, de l'autre il vous bloque en vous rappelant qu'il est un jeu, et même le maître du jeu, et que comme tous les MJ peu imginatifs, chaque initative imprévue par le système se soldera par un échec automatique de votre part. Exemple: Vous entrez dans une zone où un soldat de dos braque une civile qu'il compte violer. Vous avez un couteau de boucher et êtes préparé à l'attaquer de dos. Ben idée que n'aime pas le jeu, parce que la hitbox pour toucher un mec de dos est complètement catastrophique. Lui par contre aura tout le loisir de se tourner vers vous qui faites les cent pas en cherchant la carotide pour vous one shooter la tronche. C'est pas parce que le jeu a installé un système de dépression quand tu commets des crimes que tu peux te permettre d'en commettre autrement que là où il a prévu de te l'autoriser. Autre exemple ? Attaque de dos un civil armé d'une carabine, dont tu sais parfaitement qu'elle fonctionne, puisqu'elle t'a déjà tué dans des parties précédentes. Tue le civil, brave ton karma en baisse et ramasse l'arme. Surprise! Pas d'arme! Pas plus que de munitions. Eh oui, le jeu ne l'avait pas prévu, alors ton Maître du Jeu te dit que non et c'est tout. Arrête de faire chier maintenant. Allez, encore un exemple. Tu entres dans la maison d'un couple de vieux qui te demandent de les laisser tranquilles. La femme est malade, ils ont de la bouffe mais pas de médocs. Toi, dans ta plaque, t'as des médocs, mais tu manques de bouffe. Tu suis l'idée ? Tu reviens le lendemain (une seule visite d'un seul lieu par jour, que ça soit long ou express) pour procéder à l'échange, les bras plein d'antibiotiques pour la mémé. Ben va te faire voir, le vieux ne veut rien entendre. Tu ne peux même pas lui proposer ton idée via une interface de propostion d'échanges. Il ne fait que te suivre en te demandant de quitter sa maison. Ce lieu ne te sert en réalité qu'à t'avilir via un pillage, sous peine de t'avoir faite perdre un jour de fouille pour rien, pas à procéder au commerce équitable. Encore une fois, ce que n'a aps prévu le jeu va automatiquement te pénaliser. Et il n'a pas prévu grand chose. Prisonnier des murs invisibles plus que de la guerre présentée, tu ne vas plus chercher à survivre mais à savoir ce que TWOM te permet de faire, en tenant compte de ses limitations d'opus teubé et restrictif, au gameplay pourri pour tout ce qui concernera la baston comme si tu étais un irresponsable. C'est bien beau de mettre des embûches aux joueurs, mais dans la mesure où agir en e*foiré nous pénalise, il faut au moins nous permettre de le faire. TWOM est hypocrite en ce sens qu'il oriente grandement vos choix en vous affirmant que vous êtes libre de faire ce que vous voulez. Vous êtes un enfant sur une voiture de manège à qui on soutient que c'est lui qui conduit. Et quand on s'en rend compte, les jolis décors ne suffisent plus à alimenter la magie de l'univers. Tu sais quoi ? Ben je vais lui mettre un pouce rouge quand même. Parce que Dead in Bermuda, même s'il a exactement les mêmes défauts, se présente clairement comme une sorte de jeu de société, staté et clair sur ses règles. TWOM prétend être une expérience de guerre là où il n'est qu'une mécanique limitée avec de gros, très gros besoins d'optimisation. Un jeu superbe et qui peut emporter une part des joueurs, mais moins abouti côté fouilles que Fallout, Bioshock ou encore le tristement loupé I Am Alive. Dommage, quand on sait que la collecte d'objets est le gameplay principal du jeu. Un pouce rouge qui fait mal, qui fait râler, mais qui doit servir d'avertissement à ceux qui croiraient un peu trop vite qu'ils ont déniché la perle rare. Bon jeu malgré tout si vous le tentez, ce dont je ne peux absolument pas vous dissuader. Tout au mieux vous signaler que vous savez ce qui vous attend.", "appid": "282070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198039799317", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "227", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1516881600.0} {"text": "H1Z1 EARLY-ACCESS-REVIEW: Was soll man nur sagen??? Nach dem letzten 1,2GB Uptdate dachte ich mir: NEIN NEIN NEIN Die Updates versauen das Spiel. Es war vor etwa 10 Monaten ein Echt cooles Spiel aber jzt???Ich sage NEIN zu dem Spiel.", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198312779362", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1499947200.0} {"text": "Поебота ебаная", "appid": "885190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198102384089", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540900800.0} {"text": "(Review text hidden)", "appid": "391540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198332178362", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563451200.0} {"text": "no lo recomiendo, yo trato de jugar con un mando y esta todo desincronisado", "appid": "241930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118553203", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1539950400.0} {"text": "Jogo não roda. Dá crash assim que inicia. Win7/i5/radeon 270x. Não comprem.", "appid": "16720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076393545", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1490270400.0} {"text": "Again I wish there was something between recommend and don't recommend. The game is OKish but more on the Meh side. PROS: * Pretty graphics * Pleasant music * Bonus chapter * Easy achievements CONS: * Short, a little over 3 hours of play including the bonus chapter * Bad price - length relationship * Extremely easy * Plot so generic that doesn't spike any interest * Slow paced at the edge of boredom", "appid": "1055310", "steamid": "profiles/76561198227942340", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571400000.0} {"text": "RIP", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198314419749", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1481544000.0} {"text": "♥♥♥♥♥ game.Yes valve it is a game", "appid": "1026200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198230358608", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550491200.0} {"text": "If you like to spend countless hours in a P2W Game with bugs that exsist since the game started 10 years ago, a brocken trading system, no real support, only a couple players left and no chance to do achive anything without spending literally tens of thousands this is the game for you. Ive wasted years on this game until they broke the game multiple times with new update that where unchecked and absolutly unbalanced + straight in your face only new content for the Itemshop. Absolutly a ****show", "appid": "550900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198055308192", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1578657600.0} {"text": "O jogo era bom na época que saiu. É uma pena que foi esvaziando até desligarem os servidores.", "appid": "226700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076292185", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1376654400.0} {"text": "kısa ve öz bir şekilde almayın aldırmayın", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149962521", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1486036800.0} {"text": "Nagyon jó játék ! Csalók sincsenek benne, tökéletes anti-cheat rendszer :3", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116398144", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1492171200.0} {"text": "Wenn man sehen möchte was man alles an einem aus Arma 2 zeiten hochinteressanten game falsch machen kann sollte es unbedingt probieren. Aktuell ist es nicht mal 0,50 Cent wert.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975481357", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1533556800.0} {"text": "5 óra kínlódással eljuttam a harmadik bossig de elég volt. Unalmas , monoton.", "appid": "265300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198123388163", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484308800.0} {"text": "Thanks Gaben for turning this already piece of sh*t game into hackers realm :) Ohhh Damn valve must be itching to kill this game. You guys just made sure that Hackers won't ever have to worry about getting Vac Ban ever.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198157904951", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1509710400.0} {"text": "Easy Game. This Game gives me a headache", "appid": "476620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076048944", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591358400.0} {"text": "Good game", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118143508", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561723200.0} {"text": "ñ compre, simples.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073006583", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1427112000.0} {"text": "10/20", "appid": "224960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198264779272", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1516190400.0} {"text": "За три сотенных бумажки На ЗИЛе возил говяшки, ой-ой-ой! И скажу вам: Шеф! Вы знали! Ох и много ж вы насрали! Ой-ой-ой!", "appid": "398120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198170643289", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "17", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1533124800.0} {"text": "我第一次登录愣是花了40mins还没进去，我可去你的吧微软", "appid": "1097840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198325140928", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593518400.0} {"text": "前三章非常好玩， 后面f2p的节奏和对于作者的自我陶醉觉得无语，最后抓glitch那个环节如果不等攻击频率就秒抓永远过不去，是设计的疏忽吧。没玩过类似的就推荐，玩过类似的解密就不推荐购买。5/10", "appid": "1240210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198136398233", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597406400.0} {"text": "Выглядит как х**ня производительность как ху*ня игра ху*ня зря купил.", "appid": "346110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054178364", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592740800.0} {"text": "So!, i've beaten the game as of writing this Review. I've been a Amnesia Fan for YEARS Especially - Amnesia: The Dark Descent A Machine for Pigs was an alright Amnesia game. Either way this review is about - Amnesia: Rebirth ---------------------------------------------- I'm gonna be honest it did not feel like a \" Amnesia \" game. It felt more like a Outlast game.. But with a touch of Sci-Fi - Space stuff. It just.... didn't feel like a Amnesia game if im going to be Honest. It had some aspect of Amnesia: The Dark Descent Which felt nice seeing. Quality was / is - awesome. Atmosphere - It's awesome if you like Alien Technology. I think it was an Alright game. As i was going in thinking that it would be really familiar to the previous 2 games. But then a Alien world appeared, it kinda put me off. I did jump now and then, in the Fortress. The Fortress had some nice Jump scares, i give the game that. But seeing that The game only has 2 kind of Monsters in it is kind of a Downer. (Ghouls - Spectral) You easily got used to the 2 Monsters, which made it less scary to future encounters. ---------------------------------------------- That being said, let's wrap it up. I give the game a 5.5 / 10.", "appid": "999220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198320422220", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603281600.0} {"text": "Any other game would be constantly ridiculed if it released with keyboard controls as clunky as this game. But it's okay when FromSoft does it, right?", "appid": "814380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070271612", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604059200.0} {"text": "Es war mir nicht möglich eine einzige Runde zu spielen, noch irgendwelche nützlichen Informationen bezüglich des Status des Zählers zu ermittlen. Die Entwickler scheinen sich zu 100% abgesetzt zu haben und das einzige was man nach ewiger Recherche herausfindet ist, dass die Entwickler wohl pleite gegangen sind, das Spiel aufgegeben haben und die Server auch nicht mehr laufen. (Zumindest die für die Zähler) The Flock sollte (/dürfte) hier garnicht mehr verkauft werden, da es scheinbar komplett down ist.", "appid": "290490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198255758111", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1488628800.0} {"text": "Оптимизации в игре попросту нету !!!! rtx 2080 Ti 1080p при ультра настройке 40+ фпс ... вы гоните ?)))) Приходится с настройками возится чтобы 60+ фпс было хотя бы xD Зачем было этот шлак выпускать вообще на пк ?) Да и графика в игре хрень полная ... только природа местами красиво сделана ...персонажи это просто ппц ... вы их что в 2000х годах рисовали?))))) Не все конечно персонажи ... но большинство xD И о каких 4к может идти речь ?))))))))) Желею потраченных денег :)", "appid": "1174180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198376568443", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575806400.0} {"text": "Plain and simple, it's not a fallout game. Not really, I was willing to accept the changes made to the formula in fallout 3 and new vegas, but this is so much of a departure from the source material that it has absolutely none of the original charm. It's BARELY even a role playing game and while the voiced protagonist can push a narrative it destroys replayability and makes every single playthrough feel \" samey \" gun play is fun, but if I want a shoot 'em up I'll go pick up a platinum game. They do it better and it's at least original. DLC is a joke, no real substance here very hollow writing, it's a mess. More like Borderlands but with even MORE of that god awful anthony burch writing with even less humor. 4/10 not worth the time in the slightest if you're a fallout fan from way back. If you are ok with the aforementioned, go for it I guess, but don't expect replayability here especially with the modding scene being SOOOO dead.", "appid": "377160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044912477", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498651200.0} {"text": "nekem nem jött be", "appid": "434570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198370564666", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1534852800.0} {"text": "Complete UI ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075961756", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592136000.0} {"text": "trash.", "appid": "911400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198330137232", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554552000.0} {"text": "You should be ashamed.", "appid": "1377140", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968129065", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596974400.0} {"text": "нраица! п.с. я сильно поспешил с оценкой, ребята явно схалявили после шикарного ремейка второй части", "appid": "952060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198064208318", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585915200.0} {"text": "Oyunu bir arkadaşımla oynamak üzere indirimdeyken aldım. Oyunu uzun zamandır etrafta görüyordum ve ilgi çekici geliyordu. Ama işler umduğumuz gibi gitmedi. Oyundaki serverlere bakarken RPG ibaresi bul