 mais toujours au top. par contre ubisoft est incapable de gérer des serveurs et a la facheuse habitude de supprimer vos sauvegardes et tous ce qui va avec vous obligeant a recommencer encore et encore le jeux vous empêchant d'atteindre la fin.", "appid": "242050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198281920355", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582977600.0} {"text": "Wasted 30.00 Euro, not the best game", "appid": "107410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198137278867", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1518004800.0} {"text": "Combat is satisfying but gets repetitive, the game itself is quite short and has a really bad ending and final boss. If you play this with a friend it's an alright experience but there are so many better games to play with your friends, but atm this is the best souls like I've found to play with friends, so it's got that going for it. The difficulty it's self is not hard, except for one hidden boss which was quite a challenge. The bosses in this game were what kept me going, they did just look like big enemies but they were fun atleast. In short, good combat, bad game overall. If you want a souls like experience that's good I'd recommend salt and sanctuary.", "appid": "617290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076034868", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596283200.0} {"text": "I only brought this because the pornhub servers were down... I was expecting more nudity but I get this? Wow.", "appid": "448660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198308261655", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1489838400.0} {"text": "no.", "appid": "513000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044468966", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586779200.0} {"text": "Honestly, I'm so sad I don't like it. I've been playing TW since Rome and ammased too many hours on them: ROME: 1000+ (all on disk - recently bought in on steam) Medieval 2: 1500+ (all on disk - also bought on steam) Empire: 130+ (and about 200 more on other accounts and offline which never seemed to be added to my hours until last year ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯ ) Napoleon: 45+ Rome 2: 235+ Attila: 20+ Warhammer: 2 And I was hyped for this game. Finally TW is back with historical campaigns!!! But alas it's another let down. Since Rome 2 I feel the quality has dropped so far, Warhammer was, for me, terrible. I never understood the Warhammer battle mechanics, flying units and magic, it felt out of place for a Total War game, and this feels similar. The campaign is sort of clunkyand somewhat \"bland\". Also there are no city garrisons, unless I was doing something wrong. To top that off my favourite part of Total War... The battles... They don't last anywhere near long enough, I was fighting against a West Seaxon (West Seax?) army and I had more advanced units and more units, as soon as 30 men died in a unit they fled, no matter what, if they were mine or the enemys', I play on very hard battle difficulty so im used to a bit of wavering but they all flat out ran away and didnt rejoin, I won the battle but it didn't feel like a Total War battle. I could go into more detail but no one will read it so I'll stop here.", "appid": "712100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033844606", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525780800.0} {"text": "♥♥♥♥ game with ♥♥♥♥ servers. I submit for nanosuit and nothing. Less 3k players and servers crashing. This game is worse than critical ops and pay to win. Take off claymores or dead, because it's cancer. Too much hackers in the game. This game has more hacker than CSGO. And they do not even get banned. You can one shot with knife if you pay to win which is really cancer. Cool down on defribalator which is unrealistic and I get blacked every single time I try to launch the game.", "appid": "291480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198163404988", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570536000.0} {"text": "you need a loot bag to bag a piece of diamond and it just worth $150000", "appid": "337660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077998806", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1418904000.0} {"text": "jeux buger , depuis plusieurs mois , impossible de lancer le jeux , il plante au demarrage meme apres avoir changer de machine .", "appid": "815370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198126860737", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574769600.0} {"text": "(Review text hidden)", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198276896861", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1513080000.0} {"text": "No permite ingresar a ninguna partida, y posee multiples fallos a la hora de iniciar el juego", "appid": "489940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198271733648", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1517486400.0} {"text": "I haven't finished it yet, but I can already say that the PC port is extremely buggy and not optimized. The game itself is cool. If I can finish the game with all those bugs and low fps, I will write a positive review", "appid": "524220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198194555290", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603368000.0} {"text": "Should have been in the original BDO", "appid": "1226470", "steamid": "profiles/76561197990698410", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1590148800.0} {"text": "15 Minutes was enough for me to uninstall the game. Great concept, reminded me a lot of Fantavision for the PS2 -