ife. (╥︣﹏᷅╥)", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198150273926", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "56", "votes_funny": "21", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1442232000.0} {"text": "mic not working so i can't troll ♥♥♥♥ this game", "appid": "344760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198194684611", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1509451200.0} {"text": "So let me make another review about this game. yes it's good, yes it reminds us all of the good time of battelfield 3 and 4. Were we could change every litte detail of our gun, were the battelfields are large and open, and were we can drive vehicles like tanks and LAV (and yes you can also change every details and guns of these)... it even has that litte detail of Killstreaks usage like Call of duty, like airstrikes or spy plane for example. So yes this is the good thing about it... now the bad things. The game is badly optimzed as i still get bad fps on low settings with my Asus gtx1060 6gb, so like on point your are nicely on 60fp and then in just mere seconds you have 1fps. Also the loading times are a pain in the ass, it takes like minutes before you can finally do something, it's even worse then GTA 5. Another thing is the saves, because for some reason my loadouts just dissapears and have to start over again, it's just frustrating and annoying. So i hope this will help for most people", "appid": "674020", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100087346", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1540728000.0} {"text": "Played for 3 hours -> faction started to roll and game got interesting -> game crashed -> didn't find any autosaves -> uninstalled. This may be a great game, but I can't recommend it to anybody because the combination of random crashes and autosave turned off by default is unacceptable.", "appid": "25890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007407490", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1566648000.0} {"text": "Buggy. In the same dungeon I was: - permanently on fire - immune to explosives - getting melee'd by a boss by his shots idek how that happens also, it took me over 1000 bullets to kill a boss who I had to finish off by punching him to death. GG Bethesda this one is gold.", "appid": "1151340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198140735088", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587816000.0} {"text": "nah", "appid": "204360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198342153035", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562414400.0} {"text": "(Review text hidden)", "appid": "261640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072365984", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554465600.0} {"text": "Epic gamesde bi 10 saat falan oynadım ve bu paraya değmez. İndirimdeyken jc3 ü 6.75tl ye alın daha eğlenceli oyuna hiçbir yenilik getirmemişler sadece hortum büyük havaalanı ve yolcu uçağı(buna geç bile kalmışlardı zaten).", "appid": "517630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198392064691", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604923200.0} {"text": "Endless mode with a bunch of mods you can unlock Very repetitive, could only play an hour at a time There’s like 10 maps that you play over and over and over again, enemies spawn at random, sometimes you get ♥♥♥♥♥♥ by rng and take dmg right when you spawn because 3 reds with weapons spawned close by Only reason I finished it was the katana recall mod which I enjoyed using Just in case you wanted to go for all achievements, keep in mind that the last one requires you to wait/AFK for 2 ½ hours. Got it from humble bundle, but there is no way this is worth 25€", "appid": "690040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072240925", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598702400.0} {"text": "I dont get it", "appid": "236850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027914477", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595851200.0} {"text": "5合一次改革必卡死，严重BUG影响游戏体验，请抓紧时间修复 跟新之后还是一样啊BUG没有修复，有什么办法吗", "appid": "779340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198122213366", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1558872000.0} {"text": "So far its just so slow in development that its just not worth it. It basically feels like two guys in their basement is the only people working on this game and Bohemia Interactive doesn't really care if it take five years to get the game into beta. Then it comes down to Bohemia Interactive blaming the engine that they took a whole extra year to make and all of a sudden that engine is not strong enough for what they need. What the game need is to be open to the modding community. That what made the mod so great, there were different versions of the game and people kept on improving it more and more. I bet most of the issues would of been fixed months ago by modders.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198012308986", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1419076800.0} {"text": "EDIT: With more hours played now I have to say im still sticking with my original review. To the common player this game will get boring fast. But overall its fun. Fall Guys is an ok game. I honestly enjoy the game and believe the general audience will aswell especially if your'e a younger player BUT I feel that this game will get boring very fast....unless the developers continue adding content and improving their game. Fall Guys is a great concept and has amazing art style/audio. They could have done without the \"Battle Pass\" thing that Fortnite has but oh well. Hopefully they will continue work on this game and its not a quick cash grab. Overall I give the game a 6.5/10", "appid": "1097150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198317451910", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596542400.0} {"text": "Honestly, as savage as it sounds, the truth hurts, but Ubisoft has gotten LAZY. They no longer put in the extra effort and time to perfect their games as they have with the older titles. They used to settle for exceptional games, but nowadays they aim for just ‘okay.’ Whereas they used to focus on experience and immersion, today it’s more tailored towards money and making the series a franchise of multimedia. Too many careless and reckless bugs/mistakes in their games nowadays unfortunately. Too much copy paste, too much idle banter and grindy tasks. In my opinion, this particularly applies to Ubisoft Quebec, Both Syndicate and Odyssey, despite being fun solid games, are pretty much forgettable and don’t bring forth anything memorable or extraordinary. Both Syndicate and Odyssey lack a serious tone and include too many cringe jokes and unnecessary tasks, which evidently are forgettable and dismissible. The other games made by different developers take it more seriously, and are often better in story, gameplay, and direction. I’m sure they mean well, and by all means their optimization is superior in terms of balance and performance, as both Syndicate and Odyssey performed smoother than their previous title. Also provide beautiful worlds such as the UK and Greece. I suppose Ubisoft should really figure out each of their different branches and their cons and pros and address them accordingly. I don’t like Quebec’s direction or narrative divisions, but appreciate and admire their graphics and stability department.", "appid": "812140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034686389", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592913600.0} {"text": "ООООООООООООООООООЧЕНЬ ИНТЕРЕСНО И УВЛЕКАТЕЛЬНО", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198367033116", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529409600.0} {"text": "𝘎𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘵 𝘨𝘢𝘮𝘦, 𝘳𝘶𝘪𝘯𝘦𝘥 𝘣𝘺 𝘤𝘩𝘦𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘴.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198375380001", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511697600.0} {"text": "Taşlanmayacaksam bu oyun beni içine çekemiyor", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198271343103", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584878400.0} {"text": "Никому НЕ РЕКОМЕНДУЮ брать Character Pass к этой игре только по одной простой причины. Ужасный подбор персонажей, вот весь слитый список: Сэто Кайба (Yu-Gi-Oh!) Тощиро Хицугая (Bleach) Бискет Крюгер (Hunter x Hunter) Тощинори Яги aka Всемогущий (My Hero Academia) Маджин Буу (Dragon Ball) Кацуки Бакугоу (My Hero Academia) Учиха Мадара (Naruto) Гриммджоу Джагерджак (Bleach) Трафальгар Д. Ватер Ло (One Piece) Почему он слит? Потому что не Банкена (Кенпачи Зараки в Банкае) не Яхвача, не Торико, не Гинтамы, не Джоскэ из жожо ничего! Только Гриммджоу смогли просунуть. Лучше бы добавили Улькиорру и то в разы полезней будет.", "appid": "974726", "steamid": "profiles/76561198148019536", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "34", "votes_funny": "14", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551441600.0} {"text": "Dota Dlya Zadrota)", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198325965813", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511524800.0} {"text": "Unfortunatly, I have to give this game a bad review probably 5.5 / 10 (for now atleast). It is a good game and I love it to death, for 60 dollars though I cant say it was worth the money. It has some pretty big problems that make the game un enjoyable, atleast to me. Remeber to take this as my opinion and nothing else. First I'll start with one of the biggest things like I notice. Lack of customization. From the creators of Planet coaster, I expected more customization in the area of park design. These are a few of the things I've noticed in the customization area. Number 1. Considering these guys made planet coaster, which has loads of customization, this game is sorely lacking in that area. We only have a basic set of buildings, that, while I do enjoy the look of, are still pretty bland and un-interesting. For someone like me who loves to customize and to make things look pretty... you just cant. Everything is so bland and boring, so much empty space I can use. Number 2. In number one I just talked about buildings that would go on your mainstreet, Fast Food, Clothes Shop, Arcade, ect. For a game that is centered around building exhibits for your animals to stay in, it has only one attraction (other than the basic 2 viewing platforms) that attraction being the Gyrosphere. I like the way it looks and works however, thats all there is. In the movies we had a host of different of attractions and unfortunatly we only get one on release of this game. I expect more to be added in the future possibly as DLC or whatever so this isnt to big of an issue. Number 3. Because we are talking about the parks specificaly, I wish the people were more interesting, not so much as an issue as it is a personal preference, it just seems as though our guests are pretty bland and dont matter very much. I mean if a dino gets out and kills a bunch of people, its not a very big deal. In my experience once you get your park to that size you have so much money it doesnt even matter, you can just pay whatever you need and be done. I feel like one death should mean more than it does, if that makes sence. So i think that concludes the park side of things, this next bit is more of the animal and AI side of things. See, the game seems to have been rushed. Universal wanted to release the game along side the new movie. Unfortunatly the Frontier team wasnt able to work out all the kinks with the AI and rest of the game in that time. Number 4. Talking of AI, the dinos for one dont have very many actions. Because you will probably spend so much time watching them, the same basic interactions are really boring. They dont sleep, they dont herd, they dont play, the only things they really do is stand in this odd looking circle and roar at eachother and walk around... oh, and eat. Thats about all, they do atleast panic and run from you or your other dinos. As far as what they do while just chilling thats about all. And because they don't herd, in larger herbie exhibits, one may run off to the endge of the fence, then procede to get royally pissed off because it doesnt have any friends near it, break out, kill some people, and thats it. But it happens all the time and its super frustrating to see the popup of a broken fence right as you're about to get 5 stars and suddelny drop to 3, plus, you have even more herbies getting out and its just a big fluster cluck. The most obvious fix for this is just have a herd mentality for animals that require a herd to live happily. The AI does need alot of work. My main problems are that the dino AI is pretty bad as of now, as well as the guest AI running into enclosures :/ and I would like to see more customization for parks. Also, side note, the terrain, teraforming, and placing buildings down is complete crap. Buildings fit where they clearly shouldn't, don't where they should, its just poorly designed. Again my main points are. The dino AI needs to be refined a bit better. The dinos need more things to do such as activities. We need more attractions for our guests to take part in, like the gyrospheres. We also need more cusomization and little things to fill in sapce and add an extra level of authenticity to our parks. Obviously, aquatic and flying animals. I would also go for some new kind of transport along with the monorail. All in all I say 5.75/10 This game can be so much more and a worthy successor to JPOG it just needs a little work.", "appid": "648350", "steamid": "profiles/76561198117815553", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529496000.0} {"text": "Not enjoyable. Also, it's a game for mobile devices at best.", "appid": "294370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082509206", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601467200.0} {"text": "Dog sheet.", "appid": "209160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073262839", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520078400.0} {"text": "Just because game is ment to be simple that doesnt mean servers should be simple and crash everytime someone joins.", "appid": "674940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198195781545", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600084800.0} {"text": "aver es divertido y tiene un par de mini juegos pero el juego no da para mucho la verdad es que jugando se me iso un tanto repetitivo y aburrido ovio el juego te puede sacar unas sonrisas pero nada mas el juego en si es dificil recargar armas etc y eso aburre pues a mi opinion le falta mucho para ser un buen juego si piensas gastar tu dinero en este juego piensatelo 2 veses antes de aserlo", "appid": "657200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198329065627", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514289600.0} {"text": "Ем ну я навіть не знаю . Гра якась дуже коротка , сюжета толкового немає , сильного угара як в попередніх частинах теж немає . Заюрали створення свого персонажа і магазни одягу ,побігати можна але це вже не та гра яку всі поллюбили . Пограти можна але купляти не рекомендую", "appid": "301910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198001048041", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1422100800.0} {"text": ".........../´¯/)...............