 98.", "appid": "70", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033368192", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1478001600.0} {"text": "Сыграв в эту игру сегодня, понял - она не соперник DayZ точно. Локация не разнообразна. Понравился крафт. В будущем в DayZ тоже его добавят, поэтому DayZ всё равно будет лидировать. Играя, я не понял, что вообще произошло с миром в данной игре(радиация, зомби - так что именно вызвало апокалипсис?), видел людей, которые убивали так же, как и в DayZ, при первой встрече. Люди не меняются нигде. Пока не понятно как играть в неё. С DayZ для меня всё проще и красивее.", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084342806", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1404216000.0} {"text": "Pros: - Penguins - Good Storyline. Cons: - Freerunning is a nightmare. (no more so than any other AC game) for example, when being slightly spotted and you want to run into an alley way, Shane will randomly climb a building and hang there for funsies until you're PROPERLY spotted. - Copy & Paste of Black Flag. Ranging from general scenery (apart from ice and snow) Even the end mission is literally more or less the same. Moving platforms and deadly sunlight, Nothing creative or original. - Upgrading the ships should not be a MUST. Upgrading ships should be optional to HELP with the game. But to actually require upgrades to continue with the story is trash. Especially when it doesn't tell you you need to upgrade until you've sailed around the world twice and then when you finally get there it's like 'oh yeah. go back and upgrade lmao' - Sometimes parrying an attack, will just randomly fail for no reason at all. - The sea shanties don't sound piratey anymore :( - I miss Edward Kenway :(", "appid": "311560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067254228", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589198400.0}